title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese; add margarine at room temperature.
Cream in mixer to consistency of shortening for cake.
Gradually add flour, salt and pepper.
Use star plate or cookie press to shape.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add 7-Up.
Chill until thickens. Drain pineapple juice (save).
Fold pineapple, marshmallows and bananas in jello.
Put in pan.
Chill until firm.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix by hand!
Line 13-inch greased pan with wax paper (a must).
Pour in cake batter and bake for 1 hour in 350° preheated oven.
Turn out on board and pull wax paper away from cake.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Place all ingredients (except Bisquick, oil and milk) in crock-pot for 5 to 6 hours on low.
Drain thoroughly in colander. Save and cool liquid.
Debone chicken and cut into small pieces. Thicken liquid with flour and water paste.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Pour into oblong baking dish.
Preheat oven to 450°. Make biscuits with Bisquick, oil and milk.
(Knead 2 minutes, then cut.) Place on top of chicken and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: honey fruit compote
directions: In large bowl, combine pineapple chunks, mandarin oranges, grapes and kiwi slices.
Set fruit aside.
Add water to reserved pineapple juice to make 1 cup liquid and combine with orange juice, honey and lemon juice.
Pour over fruit mixture.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Mix the wine, butter and garlic together and pour over the shrimp.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley flakes.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for about 6 to 7 minutes.
Be careful not to overcook the shrimp.
The shrimp is done when it turns pink.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; cool.
Peel potatoes and grate.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: french stew
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a large roaster.
Cover and bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Wash and bake sweet potatoes until almost fork-tender (about 45 to 50 minutes).
Cool.
Scoop potatoes out of skins and mash, there should be about 2 cups.
Mix potatoes and remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean (50 minutes). Garnish with whipped cream.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie; preparation time: 45 minutes; cooking time: 1 1/2 hours.

title: triple good bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In medium saucepan, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Set aside.

title: anise toast
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Add anise flavoring.
Sift together flour and baking powder gradually.
Add to butter-egg mixture.
Flour board and knead dough.
Shape into large loaf divided into thirds.
Roll each in small amount of flour.
Form into loaves, pat and shape.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Slice.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: chocolate christmas treats
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Add sugar and milk.
Keep heating and stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oats, nuts and vanilla.
Allow mixture to cool to medium warm. Roll teaspoonfuls into balls.
Place on waxed paper lined cookie sheets. Chill until firm.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Mix hamburger, salt and onion in pan.
Saute until brown.
Add cubed potatoes, mixed vegetables and tomato sauce.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Stir often.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: In a medium to large saucepan, melt 1/4 stick butter or margarine and stir in 1/4 cup flour until smooth.
Add 1 cup milk and stir at a low boil until thickened and leaves sides of pan (about 2 minutes).
Remove pan from burner.
Add to this white sauce the chicken, onion, 1 egg, 1/2 cup fine bread crumbs, parsley, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Blend well. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Combine soup and 1/4 cup water.
Add 1 cup noodles, tuna, celery, cashews and onion; toss lightly.
Place in ungreased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining noodles over top. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: pineapple frozen salad
directions: Mix the first 2 items and let stand overnight.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix ingredients (except marshmallow cream) and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread marshmallow cream on cake as soon as you take from oven.
Drizzle frosting over marshmallow cream.
Cool and cut into small pieces.
Very rich.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, oleo, salt and milk.
Bring to a full boil (rolling) and boil over low heat for a full five minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add melted chocolate and Marshmallow Creme.
Add nuts and vanilla; stir until well mixed. Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cool for several hours. (Melt chocolate slowly; it burns easily.
Use heavy pan.)

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Mix all ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with mixture of 1/2 cup melted butter or margarine and crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Fold package of dry jello into cottage cheese and Cool Whip. Add crushed pineapple or fruit cocktail and mandarin oranges. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and spices; drain.
Add tomato sauce, paste and sugar.
Simmer about 1 hour on low.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Chop chicken into small pieces.
Crush chips.
Add all other ingredients, except cheese.
Mix together; pour into baking dish. Top with cheese and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese is melted good.
(Can use Velveeta cheese.)

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, butter, baking soda and salt in large bowl. Make a well in the center and add egg and buttermilk. Mix well. Blend in caraway seed and currants.
Knead until smooth, 2 to 3 minutes.
Form into 2 round balls and place on buttered cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake in 375° oven until well browned.
Cool before cutting.

title: sweet party mix
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and syrup in heavy saucepan and bring to a boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add baking soda and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour over cereal in a large bowl. Mix well to coat cereal.

title: oyster cracker do
directions: Pour oil over crackers and mix well.
Blend dry ingredients and mix with crackers.
Put in airtight container and refrigerate overnight.

title: grandma ella's apple pie
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
In bottom of unbaked pie shell, sprinkle
tablespoons flour and then sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar.
On top of this arrange the finely sliced apples.
Pour on top 3/4 cup sugar.
Then sprinkle with cinnamon.
Over this pour sweet cream.
Then dot with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Blend condensed milk, milk and water.
Add peach pulp and lemon juice.
Freeze.
This makes 2 quarts.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into large bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Gradually stir in water and vanilla until smooth and blended.
(Batter will be thin.)
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; salt to taste.
Let cool.
Skin and bone it and cut it into chunks.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute onion.
In oblong baking dish, mix tuna, onion and pepper.
Pour in soup and water.
Cook noodles until tender. Drain and add to tuna mixture.
Top with crumbled bread and shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: onion dish salad
directions: Place sliced onions in bowl.
Boil next 4 ingredients and pour over onions.
Soak overnight.
Drain well and add 1 1/2 cups salad dressing and 2 teaspoons celery seed.
Chill several hours.

title: instant hot chocolate mix(100 cups)
directions: Mix ingredients in large container.
Store in dry place.
For each cup of hot chocolate, mix 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: jubilee jumbles
directions: Mix well shortening, sugars and eggs.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Combine with sugar mixture.
Blend in nuts.
Chill 1 hour.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Frost with browned butter frosting.

title: orange jello delight
directions: Add 3 cups boiling water to Jell-O.
Mix well.
Add orange juice concentrate.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Mix.
Put in refrigerator and let set up.
Mix pudding (dry) with Cool Whip. Spread on top of set up Jell-O.
(Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese if desired.)

title: nacho sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cook over low to medium heat until cheese is melted. This is hot and delicious.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Mix all together and let set overnight in the fridge.
This will stay good for a week, if it lasts that long.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Microwave chicken breasts on High 2 minutes.
Microwave broccoli until about half done.
Layer broccoli in 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with chicken breasts and pour soup mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: five minute chili (meatless)(quick and tasty with very little fat.)
directions: Put all together and heat 4 or 5 minutes.
Serve with corn bread.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Fix Dream Whip as directed.
Blend cream cheese with 1/2 cup of powdered sugar.
Mix cream cheese mixture with Dream Whip and spread over graham cracker crust.
Then dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Stir until thick.
Pour over cream cheese and Dream Whip mixture and chill.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and buttermilk together, then, in separate bowl, mix food coloring and cocoa.
Fold into cake mixture with spoon.
Put soda and vinegar in cup; mix, then add to cake mixture with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.; cut both layers in two, making 4 layers.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy and margarine on low heat.
Mix sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking soda together.
Add to egg mixture, alternating with the buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Pour in candy and mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Shell and devein the shrimp, leaving fantail on.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Dip shrimp in mixture; place in shallow pan in single layer.
Pour remaining sauce over shrimp. Broil 6 to 8 minutes 3 inches from heat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions until done.
Drain away all grease. Place into a casserole dish that is very deep.
Add all the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° until it bubbles.
Turn oven down to 375° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put 1/2 lettuce into bowl.
Add layer of celery, onion, bell pepper, peas and eggs.
Top with remaining lettuce.
Cover with mayonnaise, spreading to sides of bowl.
Sprinkle with cheese and crumbled bacon on top.

title: savory grilled potatoes
directions: Mix salad dressing and seasonings in a large bowl until well blended.
Stir in potatoes and onion to coat.
Divide potato mixture evenly among six 12-inch square pieces of foil.
Seal each to form packet.
Place on grill and grill, covered, for 40 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: delicious dairy dip(great for fresh fruit!)
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream, sugars and syrup; beat until smooth.
Chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill for several hours or overnight before serving.

title: imitation beef stroganoff
directions: Saute diced medium onion and mushrooms.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Combine hamburger, soup, sour cream, onion and mushrooms. Cook egg noodles as directed on package.
Drain and combine with hamburger mixture.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: no fail homemade bread
directions: Scald together milk, sugar and shortening.
Remove from heat. Add 2 cups water and salt.
Let cool slightly.
Mix 1 package yeast with 2/3 cup warm milk mixture and yeast mixture.
Stir together and add remaining flour, 2 cups at a time.
Knead dough to a smooth consistency.
Let rise to double size.
Punch down and rise again. Work into rolls or loaves and place in greased pan.
Bake 1/2 hour at 400° and 1/2 hour at 350°.
Makes one 9 x 13-inch pan plus 1 loaf.

title: spicy vegetable soup
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in a large Dutch oven over medium heat until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain and return meat to Dutch oven.
Add spaghetti sauce and next 6 ingredients. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tomatoes and vegetables.
Return to boil.
Cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Yields 12 cups.

title: honey-cinnamon carrots
directions: Cook carrots with 2 tablespoons of cinnamon and drain.
Add honey and lemon juice; toss with 1 teaspoon of cinnamon more.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Mix in saucepan the pudding, sugar, milk and butter.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Take off and stir in peanuts.
Beat until starts to thicken.
Drop from teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: sweet-sour cabbage
directions: Cut medium head of cabbage in strips.
Place in large skillet; cover with water and simmer until tender.
Do not overcook.
Fry bacon cubes in another large skillet.
Remove all but 3 tablespoons of drippings.
Add approximately 2 tablespoons of flour and enough water from cabbage to make a gravy.
Add sugar and vinegar to make a sweet sour taste that pleases you.
Add salt and pepper.
Drain cabbage and add to gravy mixture.
Simmer for a few minutes.

title: norwegian pie
directions: Beat egg, vanilla and sugar.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat into first mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake in 9-inch square pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Beat heavy cream; add pineapple.
Top pie just before serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix and cook sugar, milk, flour and cocoa.
Then add egg yolks.
Cook until thick.
Turn off and add vanilla and margarine. Put in baked pie shell.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Dissolve soda with hot water.
Mix other ingredients in order. Drop by teaspoons on baking pan about 3-inches apart.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: fresh lime sugar cookies
directions: In a medium bowl with electric beater, cream butter and sugar; beat in salt and lime juice.
Add flour and stir until blended. Chill, covered tightly, until firm enough to handle.
Shape into two 4-inch long rolls.
Wrap in Saran.
Chill until firm.
Remove 1 roll at a time.
Cut crosswise into 1/8-inch slices.
Use a wide metal spatula to place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Sprinkle with sugar/lime rind mixture.
Bake at 375° approximately 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: spanish rice(serves 6)
directions: Brown hamburg; add onion and celery.
Cook until tender, not brown.
Put in casserole.
Add rice, bean sprouts, mushrooms and juice on both.
Add tomatoes and seasoning.
Bake at least 1 hour or longer at 325°.

title: "venus de milo" style soup
directions: Fry hamburg and onion in a large pan.
Add water, onion soup mix, tomatoes and vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Add orzo and cook until pasta is done.

title: tomato vegetable soup
directions: Add
all
ingredients, except zucchini and corn, to a 3 quart saucepan.
Bring
to
a boil, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes. Add
zucchini;
simmer
another 20 minutes, then add corn and cook 5 minutes more.
Serve hot.

title: kathy's lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add garlic, parsley, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer uncovered until thickened.
Cook noodles and drain.
Rinse in cold water.
Combine egg, cottage cheese, salt and pepper, parsley and the Parmesan cheese.
Alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese mixture, beef mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: skillet supper
directions: Saute pepper and onion in oil until brown.
Add hamburger; cook 5 minutes or until brown.
Add tomatoes (not drained, but chopped), water, rice and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: herbed chicken
directions: In Dutch oven, brown chicken in oil; drain.
Add carrots, mushrooms, onions, wine, water, parsley, salt, bouillon and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer with cover for 50 minutes.
Spoon off fat.

title: reuben pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine nondairy creamer, egg, onion, mustard, salt and pepper; set aside.
In large bowl, mix corned beef, sauerkraut, ground beef and bread crumbs.
Add reserved egg-onion mixture and mix with hands until thoroughly combined.
Pat 1/2 of mixture into prepared pie shell.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over top; cover with remaining mixture and sprinkle with chopped parsley, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve at once or bring to room temperature; cover with plastic wrap and freeze up to three months.
If frozen, to serve, partially thaw in refrigerator and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until heated throughout and bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: koch kase
directions: Have everything at room temperature and mix all together, except caraway seed.
Cover and let set in a warm place for one hour.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 15 minutes. (Takes a while, but it's worth it.)
Pour into a buttered dish and top with caraway seed, if desired.
Refrigerate with cover on, spread and enjoy.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in crock-pot (only fill 2/3 full).
In saucepan, melt butter; add onion.
Steam until clear, then add flour stirring constantly on medium heat.
Add milk and simmer until sauce begins to thicken; remove from heat.
Add 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Cook on low 14 to 16 hours.
Best when done the night before.
Place remainder of cheese on top.
Serve when melted.

title: pepper steak
directions: Sprinkle paprika over meat, cut in strips and let stand 10 minutes.
Cook meat and garlic in oleo until browned.
Add onions and peppers.
Cook until wilted.
Add beef broth and simmer 15 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Add to meat mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: rice broccoli dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a shallow casserole dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Then uncover and cook for another 10 minutes.

title: party pickin chicken
directions: Cut tips off chicken wings.
Halve remaining chicken wings. Combine Lipton soup mix, bread crumbs and caraway seed.
Beat egg with beer or water.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then soup mixture, coating well.
Place in shallow baking pan and drizzle with butter.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes or until tender.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl, folding together until blended.

title: teresa's hush puppy recipe
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together, then add buttermilk. Put water in the empty buttermilk container. Add to mixture a little at a time. (How much you will need depends on the weather.) This makes enough to feed 100 to 120 people.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Cook at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Stir, sprinkle on cheese and bake for 20 more minutes.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, place milk, butter, sugar, salt and cocoa (if you want chocolate fudge).
Bring to a bubbly boil.
Cook for 4 minutes and 45 seconds, stirring constantly.
Take off heat and stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until fudge starts to thicken.
Pour in square pan. Cut as desired.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order of listing.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Mix soy sauce, garlic and salad oil together.
Pour over steak; let stand 1 hour.
Pour into frypan.
Allow meat to brown thoroughly on all sides.
Add pepper, onion and celery; cover. Cook 5 to 10 minutes over low heat.
Stir in cornstarch dissolved in water; stir until thickened.
Add tomatoes; cover.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes longer or until meat is tender.
Serve over boiled rice.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as package directs.
Cook broccoli.
Put in a large casserole dish.
Add soup, broccoli, chicken and cheese.
Mix well.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake at 325° for approximately 30 minutes.
Serve with tossed salad.

title: very good and easy pickles
directions: Use a soft white cloth to tie your spices in.
Put spice bag and garlic to taste in bottom of quart jar.
Begin with a layer of pickle in jar, then a layer of sugar; continue in this manner until jar is completely filled and firmly packed.
Add tarragon vinegar, put a top on jar and begin shaking and turning the jar often until all sugar has dissolves.
Wait at least 24 hours before putting in refrigerator.
Usually takes 2 to 3 days for pickles to become crisp-firm.

title: ratatouille
directions: Cook garlic and onions in oil until tender.
Add vegetables and bay leaf.
Add salt, pepper and a little oregano.
Bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes.

title: mexican-layer dip
directions: In a medium size baking dish, spread refried beans.
Combine sour cream and taco seasoning mix for next layer.
Mash ripened avocados with guacamole mix and spread.
The other ingredients may be added for the remaining layers.
Dip is better if allowed to chill for a few hours.
Serve with taco chips.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Dissolve yeast in water. Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Knead, roll and cut with biscuit cutter.
Coat well with butter.
Let stand in a warm place for 45 minutes.
Bake at 475° until golden brown.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Mix chocolate cake mix according to directions.
Pour into greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: taco burger
directions: Brown meat.
Add taco seasoning according to directions. Spoon on roll.
Add sliced tomato, lettuce and cheese.
Serve with corn chips.

title: ground beef and vegetable stew
directions: In Dutch oven, brown beef, breaking up pieces with spoon.
Add onions, garlic, water, basil, salt, pepper and potatoes.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are almost tender.
Add peppers and tomatoes.
Simmer 10 minutes or until all is tender.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter
in
bottom
of
pan.
Sprinkle
sugar over partially drained fruit.
Measure flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and add
with milk.
Pour onto butter.
Pour fruit on top and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: lazy cobbler
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt oleo and brown sugar.
Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour over melted ingredients.
Spoon on fruit.
Cook at 325° until browned. Cinnamon or sugar may be added to fruit if desired.

title: mayfair salad
directions: Combine assorted greens, pineapple and green pepper, toss lightly.
Place in lettuce-lined bowl.
Arrange fruit salad on top. Serve with dressing.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chili sausage bake
directions: Cut margarine or butter into baking mix; refrigerate 30 minutes. Mix sausage and green chili; let stand to room temperature. Divide dough in 1/2; roll each piece to a large rectangle 1/4-inch thick. Spread meat chili mixture over dough; roll up as a jelly roll. Wrap in plastic wrap and freeze for 1 hour. Remove from freezer and slice to 1/3 inch thickness. Freeze until ready to use. Remove from freezer and place on baking sheet. Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes. Serve hot.

title: banana and cheese topping
directions: Place all ingredients in a small bowl.
Mix until smooth. Makes 1 serving as part of midday meal.
Supplement as required.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: In skillet over medium heat,
brown
meat and cook onion until done.
Pour off drippings.
Stir
in
corn, tomato sauce, rice, steak sauce and ground
pepper.
Set aside.
Cut tops off peppers; remove
seeds.
Spoon
meat
mixture
into
peppers. Arrange in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking
pan.
Bake
at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until peppers are done.

title: peach crumble
directions: Arrange peaches in a shallow, greased baking dish.
Blend remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over the peaches. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Combine flour, salt and alum.
Mix with boiling water. Add oil and mix well.
Add food coloring as desired.
Knead with flour to stiffness desired.
Keep covered when not in use.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt, pepper and mustard.
Place bread crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble sausage over bread.
Add cheese and mushrooms.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Refrigerate 8 to 10 hours.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted margarine; line 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Dissolve together jello, boiling water and lemon juice; cool.
Add jello mixture to cream cheese mixture, then fold in 1 large can Milnot evaporated milk (whipped).
Pour over graham cracker crust. Sprinkle a few graham cracker crumbs on top.

title: congealed lime salad
directions: Soften cream cheese (room temperature).
After adding water to Jell-O, work in cream cheese until blended.
Add other ingredients and chill.
Use Bundt pan or mold.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Make a graham cracker crust by combining the graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter and pat into a 9 inch pie plate. Bake at 300° for 12 - 15 minutes.
Cool.
Partially thaw the lemonade and combine with the sweetened condensed milk.
Fold in Kool Whip and pour into a graham cracker crust.
Chill for at least one hour.
Can be garnished with a lemon cartwheel.

title: hush puppies
directions: In a medium bowl mix the cornmeal, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Then stir in the onion.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix melted butter and sugar; add eggs and mix by hand.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese-olive dip or spread(heloise's recipe)
directions: Mix cream cheese with mayonnaise.
Stir in pecans, olives, olive liquid and pepper.
It will be a little mushy but will thicken in the refrigerator. The spread will keep for weeks.
It makes a great spread for crackers or finger sandwiches.
(Also, low calorie cream cheese and mayonnaise can be used with good results.)

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Melt stick of oleo; add crushed Ritz crackers.
Place crackers in bottom of oblong baking dish.
Layer drained beans and corn. Mix soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, onion and salt.
Spread over beans and corn.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: tomato ham soup
directions: Boil ham for 1 to 2 hours.
Separately cook macaroni until tender and drain.
Remove ham from broth and cut up in small pieces, put back into broth.
Add the macaroni, tomato juice and pepper to taste.
Serves 6.
Can freeze.

title: emma's blueberry buckle
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg, and stir in milk.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend in blueberries.
Put in greased pan.

title: hot chili dip
directions: In medium skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Blend in soup mix and sour cream.
Add chili powder to Ro-Tel that has been beaten until smooth.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Add salt to taste.

title: leona's sugar free apple pie
directions: Combine apple juice, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir sliced apples into mixture and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes more.

title: three layer delight
directions: Melt margarine and mix in flour and nuts.
Spread evenly on bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool completely.

title: blueberry cheesecake bites
directions: Break the graham cracker in half crosswise. Spread 1 tablespoon of the cream cheese spread onto each graham cracker. Top each with a strawberry slice.

title: shepherd's bread
directions: Slice off top of bread.
Hollow out center, leaving 1 to 2-inch shell.
Combine remaining ingredients in microwave-safe dish.
Mix well.
Microwave just until heated.
Fill center with cheese mixture.
Wrap in
foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 24 servings.

title: half and half deli pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot; add washed cukes.
Cover top with foil.
Let stand 2 days (stir).
Will keep fresh in refrigerator in jars or plastic containers for about 2 weeks.

title: ginger-fruit punch(non-alcoholic)
directions: Combine all ingredients into punch bowl.
Serve with a frozen fruit ring.

title: whole wheat muffins*
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, including raisins.
Make a well in center and add egg, oil and yogurt or buttermilk.
Mix until dry ingredients are moistened, adding fruit juice as needed.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 full.
It is not necessary to grease tins.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 muffins.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Cut in margarine.
Mix sour cream and skim milk together; add to flour mixture.
Knead and cut.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Contains 130 calories.

title: golden cliff cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla and egg yolks.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add dry ingredients to egg yolk mixture alternately with milk. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 25 minutes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch loaf pan.

title: perdue's delmarvalous chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients first.
Then add vinegar and stir well. Next add beaten egg.
Stir well.
Add cooking and oil and stir.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry items together.
Add oil and buttermilk; mix well. Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix together with all other items.
Cover; must be refrigerated.
Use as needed; this will keep 10 days to 2 weeks.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and add to the buttermilk.
Mix in other dry ingredients. Make biscuits by rolling dough and cutting them out.
Let rise about 10 minutes or longer before baking. Refrigerate any leftover for the next day.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: lemon bundt cake
directions: Blend all at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Cool 1/2 hour before removing.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Fry bacon; saute onion and mushrooms in bacon grease.
Add vinegar, sugar and 1 tablespoon water; heat to slight boil.
Pour over fresh spinach.
Add boiled eggs, salt, pepper and Tabasco and toss well.
Stir in bacon chips.
Serve immediately.

title: sugarless drop cookies
directions: Combine all ingredient except raisins and nuts in large bowl and mix well.
Add raisins and nuts and mix gently.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until brown.

title: scotch friendly bread
directions: Whip and beat until fluffy, putting vanilla in before the flour.
Mix flour in a little at a time.
Place in two ungreased square pans.
Dampen palms of hands and spread batter out.
Prick it clear through with hot, wet fork.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cut in diamond shape.

title: fake strawberry preserves
directions: Mash figs.
Mix all ingredients; heat on low.
Boil on low with lids on jars for 20 minutes.
Should seal.
Serve with English muffins, toast or peanut butter sandwiches.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Mix softened cheeses and all other ingredients together.
Form 2 rolls and roll in chopped nuts.

title: quick artichoke pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water (drain again).
In a large bowl, add pasta, artichokes and marinade, mushrooms, tomatoes, olives, parsley, and basil.
Toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Before serving, season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serves 6.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings. Simmer slowly for 20 minutes.
Boil noodles.
Drain.
Mix all together.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: black forest cake
directions: Bake cake according to manufacturer's directions in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Mix pie filling and almond flavoring.

title: billy goat cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and water.
Beat well.
Add flour, soda and spices.
Mix well.
Add ground raisins and nuts.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: chicken 'n rice
directions: Mix all but chicken and place in greased casserole.
Place chicken breasts on rice.
Salt, pepper and paprika to taste. Bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes and onion in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Mix mushroom soup and milk; pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake in a moderate 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in large dishpan in order given.
Drop by large spoon and flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Don't overbake these cookies.
They freeze well.
This recipe may be divided in half.

title: super squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion in salted water.
Drain.
Add sour cream and soup.
Melt butter; add dressing.
Grease casserole dish and spread half of dressing mix over bottom.
Pour in squash and cover with rest of dressing.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy green bean casserole
directions: Add soup, cheese and sauces to sauteed onions.
Stir and add pimentos.
Place beans in casserole and pour sauce over them.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbles.

title: bean casserole
directions: Put celery, onions and ground meat into casserole; bake in oven 20 minutes at 425°.
Remove loosen meat; add ketchup, water, salt, garlic salt and beans.
Place in oven for additional 25 minutes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt margarine in a baking dish; layer with wafer crumbs, chocolate pieces, nuts and coconut.
Drizzle condensed milk over all and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls to cover a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool completely.
While pizza crust (crescent rolls) is cooling, mix together softened cream cheese, dry package of Ranch dressing and mayonnaise.
Mixture will be of medium texture, easy to spread.
Chop finely about 1/2 cup of your choice of 2 vegetables.
Spread mixture over cooled pizza dough. Sprinkle diced vegetables over mixture.
Cover with layer of shredded cheese. Refrigerate for several hours.
Cut into small squares.

title: tomato jelly
directions: Heat tomato juice to boiling.
Add Sure-Jell.
Boil 2 minutes. Add sugar and boil 4 minutes.
Quickly add Jell-O.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare gelatin as directed on package, using 1 1/2 cups of water. Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly. Spoon into a 10-inch mold ring and refrigerate until firm. Unmold on a cold platter. Yields 10 servings.

title: plain waffles
directions: *Hint:
For the very lightest pancakes or waffles, replace the milk with club soda.
Close windows before cooking, or waffles or pancakes will float out!

title: biscuits with chicken
directions: Bake biscuits until light brown. Mix chicken and soup together and pour over browned biscuits. Return to oven and heat until soup is bubbly. Serve with favorite vegetables.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cooking Time: 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese with a mixer; add powdered sugar, beating until smooth, then add peanut butter and milk, again beating until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into pie shells.
Refrigerate or can be put in freezer for 4 to 6 hours.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Blend milk, cream cheese and sour cream in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Put in casserole and cover with pecans which have been sauteed in the butter.
(Skip the sauteing and toss them on top to save the calories.) Need not be exact on amounts.
Bake in small casserole for 20 minutes at 350°. Eliminate baking to serve cold.

title: apple pie supreme
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Core.
Peel apples.
Cut in pieces. Simmer apples, 1/4 cup sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg until apples are just tender, 1 or 2 minutes.
Add cornstarch which has been dissolved in cold water.
Simmer approximately 5 minutes.
Cool. Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Blend in flour until crumbly to make topping.
Pour cooled apple filling over graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle topping over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain well.
In a large mixing bowl combine cooked tortellini, sweet pepper, broccoli, carrot and olives.

title: marinated turkey
directions: Buy whole turkey breast; remove all skin and bone.
Cut into pieces about the size of your hand.
Refrigerate turkey in marinade at least 8 hours or up to 48 hours; the longer it marinates, the less cooking time it takes.

title: easy bundt cake
directions: Blend ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken spread
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and serve with crackers, etc.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes, onions and salt in just enough water to cover. Cook until tender; mash potatoes lightly with potato masher.
Add butter and melt.
Add milk and celery seed or powder, if desired. Cook until hot and serve.
We like to add homemade egg noodles for a change.

title: pumpkin chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat baking sheets lightly with nonstick cooking spray. Cream together the margarine and sugar. Add egg, vanilla and pumpkin.

Mix well. Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and chocolate chips. Stir into creamed mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls on baking sheet. Bake in preheated oven 13 to 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: chipped beef spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill 2 hours.
Serve with crackers or cocktail rye bread.

title: jellied tuna with mayonnaise
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in warm water.
Add vinegar and salt.
Chill. When slightly thickened, fold in remaining ingredients.
Blend. Turn into individual molds or 1 large one.
Chill until firm. Unmold on lettuce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onion together; drain.
Mix all ingredients together in pan where noodles are cooked.
Pour in large deep round or square baking dish that has been greased.
Put grated cheese on top and bake at 350° (or microwave) until cheese is melted and all ingredients are hot.
(This will make 2 dishes full.)

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter, milk and salt in saucepan and bring to a rolling boil.
Boil one minute, then remove from heat and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let stand until cool and firm; remove from paper. Ready to eat.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot-sweet mustard
directions: Combine mustard and vinegar.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, combine that with the sugar and eggs in a double boiler. Cook until thickened.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water, about 45 minutes.
Debone and cut into bite sized pieces.
Layer chicken and thawed broccoli cuts in a Pyrex 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole, mixing gently.
In medium bowl, mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Spread on top of chicken and broccoli.
Top with bread cubes and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
May be frozen.
Bake thawed.

title: sweet potato casserole(from barbara deskins)
directions: Heat potatoes and pour off liquid.
Add margarine, sugars and salt.
Adjust amount of sugar to individual taste.
Mash potatoes with mixer.
Beat eggs and mix in potatoes.
Add milk until consistency is similar to regular mashed potatoes.
Add vanilla.

title: pasta salad surprise
directions: Chill Veg-All thoroughly.
Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Drain; combine macaroni, Veg-All, bacon and 1/2 can of onion rings.
Add mayonnaise, 1/2 of the parsley and seasoned salt.
Toss gently.
Serve immediately or chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: candied walnuts
directions: Combine sugar, water and orange juice in saucepan and stir until blended.
Cook slowly until small amount forms a ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Make sure nuts are coated.
Pour out on waxed paper or cookie sheet and separate with fork.
Cool and store refrigerated in tightly covered containers.

title: sunday's deer steak
directions: Season, flour and dip in melted shortening or oleo. Lay on bread pan or cookie sheet. Place in 200° oven while at Sunday school or church (2 hours total). Turn oven to 350° to brown or place under broiler for a few minutes.

title: b's new england clam chowder
directions: Wash and open the clams, reserving the liquid.
In a large pot saute the bacon over low heat.
When bacon is cooked through, remove the slices and reserve.
Mince the clams and the onion. Saute the clams and the onion in the bacon fat in the pot.
Add the thyme.
Sprinkle flour into the mixture.
Add clam juice, bay leaves, pepper (if you like) and the diced potatoes.
Crumble and add the reserved bacon strips.
Cook until potatoes are tender. Add milk, cream and butter.
Do not let mixture boil at this point. Correct seasoning.
Enjoy!
(Makes about 4 to 6 servings.)

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Let cheese and butter soften to room temperature.
Add vanilla. Sift sugar in mixture while beating with mixer.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans and coconut.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and shape in ball. Chill in refrigerator 2 hours, then roll in the 1 1/2 cups chopped nuts.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients as listed in order.
Pour into 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bolt and nuts
directions: Melt butter and add sauces.
Pour over mixed cereals and nuts in shallow pan, (9 x 13 x 2-inch) or larger.
Sprinkle with seasoned salts.
Bake in a slow oven at 300° for 30 minutes.
Stir carefully every 10 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Tear up 4 slices of bread and place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon sausage over bread. Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour over mixture in the dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
The cheese will rise to the top.
This can be made the night before, refrigerated and baked the next morning. Serves 6 to 8.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Mix all but cheese and chips.
Put in casserole.
Sprinkle cheese, then chips on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dough for fried pies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in butter with knife or blender until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Mix egg yolk and milk; stir in flour, adding only enough to hold the dough together. Shape into a ball.
Wrap in wax paper and chill 1 hour.
Roll out to 1/16-inch thick.
Place 1 1/2 tablespoons filling in center and fold over.
Moisten edges with cold water.
Press with fork.
Fry at 315° for 2 or 3 minutes on each side in hot oil.

title: pork jambalaya
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
In a small lightly greased ovenproof skillet, brown chops on both sides.
Remove chops; set aside.
Pour off all but 2 teaspoons drippings.
Add celery, scallions and green pepper.
Saute until tender.
Stir in rice, broth and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Return chops to pan. Cover; bake in 375° oven for about 30 minutes or until chops are tender.
Fluff rice with fork.
Makes 2 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies into fine crumbs; set aside.
Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar in separate bowl.
Mix pudding and milk well. Combine the cheese mixture and pudding in large bowl.
Add Cool Whip.
In large pan or bowl, alternate layers of cookies and pudding, starting and ending with cookies.
Refrigerate until served.
Can be decorated with gummi worms or flowers and served with a trowel.

title: tuna fish with rice
directions: Cook rice in double boiler.
Add butter and salt.
Mix lightly.
Line well-oiled with rice.
Pour tuna fish into rice mold.
Cover with white sauce which has been combined with the egg.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
(If desired, minced beef, chicken or salmon may be used instead of tuna.)

title: seven-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix all ingredients and pour 1 1/2 cups batter per pan and bake for 15 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage and celery in water for 8 minutes and drain.
Add chopped onion.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes, preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all except corn flakes and 1/4 c. melted oleo.
Place in 3 qt. casserole or large baking dish.
Sprinkle buttered flakes over top and bake 45 minutes.
Serves 10-12.

title: hillbilly apple cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Time depends on the variety of apples used.
Some are juicier so test cake with cake tester or toothpick until it tests done.

title: crispy nut shortbread
directions: Heat oven to 300 degrees.
Grease 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy; blend in egg and vanilla.
Add meal, flour and nuts; mix well.
Spread onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until edges are golden brown.

title: tostada dip
directions: Add or take away portions according to taste.

title: old settler baked beans
directions: Brown and drain hamburger, bacon and onion.
Drain and mix other ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: whoppers candy milkshake
directions: Mix in blender and serve.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well. Add flour, soda and sour cream, alternately.
Add vanilla. Bake in tube pan which has been greased and floured for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Start checking baking time at 1 1/4 hours.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown meats in hot fat; add soy sauce and 1 cup water.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Add celery and onion; simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Blend cornstarch and water; stir into meat mixture.
Add chestnuts, bean sprouts and mushrooms; heat through.
Season.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: shrimp cocktail rolls
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add yeast.
Let stand 5 minutes; mix well.
Blend in flour, a little at a time, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours or overnight before serving.
(On rubens, this dressing is great.)

title: anise cookies
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oleo.
Add soda, cream of tartar, oil and vanilla, then add flour.
Make into big balls; chill 1 or 2 hours.
Flour and cut out.
Bake at 325° for 4 to 6 minutes.

title: chicken elegante
directions: Combine stuffing mix, water and 2 tablespoons butter.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Mix gravy, mushrooms and wine; set aside.
In skillet/oven, lightly brown chicken in 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Place in baking pan; top each piece with stuffing, broccoli and gravy mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: e-z dinner muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together in a bowl.
Grease muffin pans well. Spoon into pans.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate marvel pie
directions: Melt and blend the chocolate chips, sugar and milk.
Cool. Separate the eggs.
Beat the egg whites.
Beat in, one at a time, the egg yolks, then the vanilla or rum flavoring.
Fold in the beaten egg whites.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: italian beef casserole
directions: Brown
meat
and
mushroom
pieces.
Drain
excess oil. Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Add all ingredients except
cheese and mix well.
Put thin layer in casserole dish, 9 x
13-inch.
Sprinkle with half of both cheeses.
Add remaining mixture
and
sprinkle again with remaining cheese. Bake at
350° for
minutes, if using immediately.
If for future use,
cover tightly
with
foil wrap before baking and freeze.

title: italian scallops
directions: Combine olive oil, butter and garlic.
Coat scallops with mixture and let marinate 1 to 4 hours at room temperature.
In a large skillet, heat 1 inch of oil to 350°.
Bread scallops and fry in oil, about 2 minutes on each side.
Place on paper towels. Serve with lemon wedges and cocktail sauce for dipping.
Use as main course or an appetizer.

title: c.y.m.  brownies
directions: Hey kids, this is so easy to make and Mom usually has all the ingredients in the kitchen, except the cocoa, so buy some cocoa and enjoy brownies for a long time.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and toss.
Pour Ranch dressing over and toss again.
Pour warm bacon drippings over and toss.
Refrigerate for 1 hour and serve.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with margarine over low heat.
Remove. Gradually blend in milk.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt together; add beaten eggs and vanilla to dry mixture.
Blend into chocolate mixture.
Pour into unbaked 10-inch pie shell.
Mix the coconut and pecans; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until top is puffed.
Filling will be soft but will set while cooling.
Cool 4 hours before serving.

title: easy oven meatballs
directions: Place in greased or Pammed 13 x 9-inch metal baking pan. Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine bread crumbs, onion, turkey, spinach, salt, pepper and egg.
Shape into 16 meatballs. Place in greased or Pammed 13 x 9-inch metal baking pan.
Bake about 25 minutes until meatballs are lightly browned and cooked thoroughly.
Heat pasta sauce.
Add cooked meatballs and simmer 10 minutes to blend flavor.
Serve over rice or spaghetti.

title: swedish roasted potatoes
directions: Slash potatoes into thick slices, but do not cut all the way through.
Add seasoning to hot water and pour over potatoes. Baste while cooking.
About 15 minutes before removing from the oven, drain off most of the broth and thicken slighlty with flour. Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in oven at 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: ricotta pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with a mixer on low for 2 minutes. Add eggs, milk and extracts and mix 1 more minute.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fried chicken
directions: You will need 1 large iron skillet.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies cereal, stir well until coated.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, melt the butter.
Add honey, mustard and curry powder and mix well. Coat both sides of chicken pieces with the honey mixture as you place them in the pan, skin side down.
Bake for 1/2 hour on each side, basting occasionally.
Serve with rice.

title: 3 cheese lasagna
directions: Brown beef and set aside.
Boil lasagna noodles and set aside. Layer ingredients one by one into buttered cake pan until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Measure soda and buttermilk into quart size bowl.
Beat together "until it sounds thick."
Stir in blackberry jam and molasses.
Set aside.
Cream butter, adding sugar and beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each.
Have ready the 1 cup of flour sifted with spices.
Add this cup of flour and spices.
Add blackberry jam mixture.
Mix well. Add 2 cups of flour gradually.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Blend well.
Last of all, fold in raisins, cherries and nuts floured in remaining 1/2 cup of flour.
Stir just to mix evenly. Pour into 10-inch tube pan lined with wax paper and lightly greased.
Spread evenly on the top.
Bake in low oven (300°) for 1 hour.
Reduce heat to 275° and continue baking (without peeking!) another hour.
Turn on cake rack to cool.
Test for doneness before turning.

title: kentucky fried chicken
directions: *Combine pancake mix with paprika, sage and black pepper.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: *You must use one of these to get the true flavor of this casserole.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream the butter with the sugar.
Beat in the eggs.
Add the melted chocolate, vanilla, grated orange rind and the milk.
Stir in the grated zucchini.

title: skillet beef stew
directions: In saucepan, cook noodles and drain.
In medium bowl, combine soy sauce, catsup, cornstarch and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Add flank steak to mix and stir until covered.
In skillet over medium-high heat, add 2 teaspoons of oil and cook carrots and onions until crisp and lightly browned.
Remove to another bowl.
In same skillet over high heat, add 2 more teaspoons of oil.
Cook mushrooms until tender and liquid evaporates.
Remove to bowl with carrots and onions.
Add steak to oil with mixture.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Stir in veggies and 1/2 cup of water; heat through. Stir occasionally.
Serve over noodles.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Cut veal into serving pieces.
Cook onion and garlic in 3 tablespoons olive oil for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and oregano.
Simmer 20 minutes longer.
Combine crumbs and 1/4 cup of grated cheese.
Dip veal into egg, then into crumbs.
Brown in 3 tablespoons olive oil in skillet.

title: strawberries and cream
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries. Stir occasionally until thawed.
Add crushed pineapple and bananas which have been diced.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a large glass bowl.
Chill until firm.
Decorate with cream, if desired.

title: orange julius
directions: Fill blender with water, juice, malt and sugar; blend together.
Serves 4.

title: baked cornbread dressing
directions: Bake Homestead Yellow Cornbread (see recipe in this cookbook), crumble when cool in a 2-quart bowl.
Lightly brown onions and celery in margarine or butter.
Add eggs, pepper and poultry seasoning to the crumbled cornbread.
Add the onions and celery. Add chicken or turkey stock.
Stir and pour into a well-greased pan (6 or 8-inch square).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or browned to your liking.

title: chili beans
directions: In skillet, cook meat, stirring until brown.
Discard excess fat.
Add 1/2 cup onion.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs one at a time and pour into ingredients.
Add milk, vanilla, melted margarine and corn; mix well.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed bundt pound cake
directions: Bake in greased (not floured) pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn out of pan and glaze with 1 cup 10x sugar and 3 tablespoons lemon juice.
Do this while cake is still warm.

title: picante chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt; set aside.
Cook onion and garlic in oil in 10-inch skillet 2 minutes.
Add chicken broth and salsa.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Arrange chicken breasts over rice.
Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, until all liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes. Garnish with tomato, avocado and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips or soft flour tortillas.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Put 1 teaspoon soda in 1/4 cup hot water.
Add cinnamon, allspice and vanilla.
Mix well.
Nuts or raisins may be added. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: walnut waffles
directions: Combine eggs, milk and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add wet ingredients to dry.
Add melted butter. Whisk until batter is smooth, but do not overmix.
Nuts can be added at this point, or sprinkled on waffle prior to cooking. Cook waffles until golden brown.
Top with whipped cream and grated walnuts, if desired.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in 1 cup boiling water. Add 2 1/2 cups cold water. Add blueberries and pineapple.
Let jello set.

title: almond chicken
directions: Remove bones and skin from chicken.
Pound flat with heavy pan; cut in half.
Arrange slice of cheese and ham on each piece of chicken.
Fold short sides over filling; roll up lengthwise. Secure with wooden toothpicks.
Dust with flour; dip into beaten egg.
Coat with crumbs.
Arrange rolls on microwave tray or baking dish; dot with butter.
Cover lightly with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Uncover; microwave 2 minutes more or until chicken is tender.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Peel shrimp.
Mix together shrimp, tomato, onion, garlic, and jalapeno.
Stir in olive oil and parsley; season to taste with salt and pepper.
Top with sliced avocado.
Serves 4.

title: taco soup
directions: In a large saucepan, brown beef and onion; drain.
Add corn, tomatoes, kidney beans, tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with corn chips, cheese and/or sour cream, if desired.
Yield 4 to 6 servings (1 1/2 quarts).

title: veal chops parmesan
directions: Season the chops to taste with salt, pepper and garlic.
Put bread crumbs and cheese in one bowl.
In another bowl, put eggs, milk and salt.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake at 350° until brown on top (approximately 20 to 25 minutes). Serve with Club crackers.

title: chocolate bar
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on waxed paper.
Freeze.
Can be divided into small servings.
A good snack.

title: oriental vegetable soup
directions: In a pot, combine vegetables, garlic and ginger.
Saute 10 minutes in 1/2 cup broth.
Add all the rest of the ingredients. Simmer 1 minute.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Spread buttered tortillas in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Spread all of chicken over tortillas.
Sprinkle half of cheese over chicken.
In a saucepan, put onions, chilies, oleo, soup and milk. Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over chicken layers.
Add another layer of tortillas and rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or cover and freeze for later.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Melt cheese in top of double boiler.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly; roll into small balls.
May be frozen at this point or baked at 375° until lightly browned.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Grease 2 (15 1/2 x 12-inch) baking sheets.
Keep warm.
Put sugar, syrup and water in a 3-quart casserole.
Cook in microwave oven on Full Power for 8 to 10 minutes or until soft ball stage. Stir occasionally while cooking.
Stir in peanuts.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until hard ball stage.
Stir in butter and soda. Pour half of candy on each sheet, spreading to 1/4-inch thick. Cool.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In large roasting pan with lid, mix onion soup mix, mushroom soup, milk, and hot water together. Add rice, mix well. Lay chicken pieces on top of liquid mixture. Cut butter over top. Cover pan. Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 -2 hours. Rice should be soft, some liquid. Don't cook too long or rice will be dry. Start checking for doneness after 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple streusel pie
directions: Place apples in pie shell and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cream 4 tablespoons of butter, sugar and eggs; add salt, vanilla flavor and cream cheese until just smooth.
Pour over apples.
Combine brown sugar, flour, 4 tablespoons butter and pecans.
Crumble this mixture on top of pie.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue to bake for 15 minutes.

title: apple pumpkin dessert
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Spoon apple filling into 8 to 10 custard cups.

title: lemon-frosted gingerbread cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon, cloves and salt. In another bowl, mix margarine, egg, molasses, vinegar and milk until smooth.
Add dry ingredients to this mixture, beating well. Cover.
Chill 1 1/2 hours.

title: crunchy cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and break cauliflower into flowerets.
Combine with next 3 ingredients in medium mixing bowl.
Toss gently.
Stir together remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Stir well.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Cover and chill.
tags: Hidden Valley buttermilk salad dressing mix

title: pacific salmon with roasted garlic
directions: Separate garlic into cloves and peel. Place in small ramekin and cover with olive oil. Wrap with foil. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Place garlic and 1 tablespoon of oil from baked garlic in food processor. Add butter and puree; season with salt and fresh ground pepper.

title: fagioli
directions: Rinse and pick over beans.
Place beans and water in
a stock pot; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Cover and let sit one hour.
Return to heat and simmer 1 hour longer. Drain, reserving 2 cups liquid.
Set aside.
Brown meat, onions, garlic, carrots and green pepper in the pot.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Return beans and reserved liquid to the pot.
Cook 1 hour.
Add cooked macaroni and a splash of wine. Serves a crowd and freezes well.

title: savory green beans
directions: Combine vinegar, salt, pepper and dill weed.
Combine bacon, onion and remaining combined ingredients and pour over beans in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or microwave until done.

title: italian zucchini soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown sausage with onion; drain excess fat. Add the celery, green pepper, sugar, salt, basil, oregano, pepper and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Add zucchini; simmer 1/2 hour or more.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired. Yield: 2 quarts.

title: party salad
directions: Prepare cherry Jell-O according to package directions and let congeal.
Combine Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients along with Jell-O (cut into small pieces).
Toss to mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry cheese cake squares(great for christmas or valentine's day)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a
13 x 9-inch pan, combine graham cracker crumbs and margarine.
Press into bottom and up sides of pan. Bake 10 minutes. Set aside.
In medium bowl with electric mixer on medium speed, beat pudding mix, cheese, dry milk, sugar, vanilla and 1 1/2 cups water until blended.
Pour over crust.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine fruit cocktail, bananas, apples, grapes, cherries and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream; refrigerate.
Just before serving, garnish with strawberries.

title: congealed applesauce salad
directions: Heat applesauce; add cherry jello and cool.
Add ginger ale and orange juice.
Congeal.

title: old fashioned barbecue ribs
directions: Brown ribs in iron skillet.
Mix ketchup, water, brown sugar, vinegar and onion.
Pour over ribs in baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add catsup, chili powder and beans.
Cover with grated cheese and onions last.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Delicious with taco chips!

title: natural room freshener
directions: Place cinnamon in a large pot with water and orange rind. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer.
The combination of cinnamon and orange will fragrance every room in your home.
It will smell clean, fresh and delicious.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in heavy skillet; saute celery and onion until tender.
Pour into greased casserole.
Dribble soup over.
Add cheese and rice; stir in salt and cooked broccoli.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about an hour.

title: i can't believe it's a cookie
directions: Roll tablespoon of dough in a ball.
Dip fork in sugar and press to flatten cookie.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: eggplant chutney
directions: Peel and chop eggplant.
Core and chop apples.
Finely chop onions.
Put the pickling spice in cheesecloth.
Put all ingredients in pan, except sugar, and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes. Add sugar and simmer until thick and lustrous.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients. Put in Pam sprayed casserole and top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° until it bubbles.
Remove from oven and spread French fried onions on top.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: beef stick
directions: Mix well and form into 2 rolls.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple and bring to a boil.
Add marshmallows, stir and cool for a few minutes.
Add sour cream and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add sugar if needed.
Pour into Jell-O mold and chill.

title: german slaw
directions: Alternate a layer of cabbage with a layer of onions.
Put 7/8 cup sugar on top.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over cabbage and cool completely.
Refrigerate. Next day, stir and repeat for 3 days.
Can also be eaten immediately.

title: hanky pankys
directions: Brown meat in large skillet; season with garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Make sure meat is in a crumbly texture. After meat is cooked, place chunks of cheese on top and cover pan with lid.
Simmer on low until the cheese melts and stir mixture thoroughly.
Spoon meat mixture on party rye slices and serve warm.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Add all ingredients together except onions using only 1/2 of these now.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 1/2 hour, then add remaining 1/2 of onions on top.
Don't stir.
Bake until onions are crunchy, about another 5 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff.
Add pinch of salt and vanilla.
Add red or green food coloring if you like.
Fold in pecans, cereal and coconut. You may use corn flakes or miniature chocolate chips if desired.

title: chicken pot pie casserole
directions: Mix together margarine, flour and milk.
Set aside. Combine all other ingredients. Pour into 3-quart casserole dish.
Pour first mixture on top for crust. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until crust is brown.

title: toasted and seasoned pecans
directions: Heap pecans in middle of cookie sheet.
Pour melted butter or margarine over pecans and sprinkle onion salt or powdered on pecans.
Mix this mixture around with a fork or spoon and spread to all corners.
May want to add regular salt to taste.
Bake at 200° for about 1/2 hour.
Turn with spatula every 15 minutes. Bake until lightly toasted.
Delicious!

title: hot dog stew
directions: In stew pot filled 1/2 with water, put in peeled whole potatoes, carrots and whole peeled onions.
Add salt and pepper to water and taste.
When potatoes and other vegetables are almost cooked, add frankfurters and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with French or Italian bread.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat one large chopped onion with frozen broccoli and oleo until onion is tender and broccoli is thawed (you can put in 1/2 cup of celery with onion, if desired).
Add milk, Cheez Whiz and cream of chicken soup.
Bring to a boil.
Measure 1 cup of regular rice, before it is cooked, and cook as directed.
Mix cooked rice and broccoli mixture together.
Put in a casserole pan and bake at 375° until bubbly hot.

title: chicken biscuit pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Stir soup; add water.
Slowly blend in chicken, peas and pimento.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hobo vegetables
directions: Cut 4 pieces of foil. To each piece, add 1 carrot, 1 onion, 1 potato and 1 tbsp. butter; salt & pepper to taste. Wrap snugly and seal. Bake on a cookie dish at 350 degrees for 45 60 minutes or until done.

title: kool-aid frosty winter fizz
directions: Mix soft drink mix with water.
Add ice cream.
Stir until melted.
Just before serving, pour in carbonated beverage.
Makes 32 servings, 1/2 cup each.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in serving size.
Put in pan and almost cover with water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until tender, but not soft.
Place in a baking pan.
Slice 1 medium size orange thin; add to syrup.
Cook until syrup drops heavy off spoon.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: agnes party rolls
directions: Melt first 5 ingredients together.
Split dinner rolls and spread on both sides.
Place a slice of ham and cheese in each roll.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: curried shrimp dip
directions: Mix in blender or food processor and add more mayonnaise if necessary.

title: easy ice cream
directions: In a pint-sized Ziploc bag, put milk, sugar and vanilla in bag. Mix well.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate. Drain peaches and arrange on top of crust mixture leaving 1/2-inch between the sides.
Combine cream cheese, peach juice, sugar and vanilla and spread on top of peaches.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 300°
for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool and enjoy.

title: meat loaf(for 50 people)
directions: Mix well and pack firmly into greased loaf pans, 3/4 full. You will need 3 loaf pans, about 12 x 4-inch. Bake in moderate oven for 1 hour.

title: hot fudge pudding cake(no fat)
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa and baking powder.
Blend in milk, applesauce and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In small bowl, combine remaining sugar, brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Pour hot water over top.
Do not stir.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken fried steak and milk gravy
directions: Season meat with salt
and
pepper in shallow dish with flour and 1 teaspoon
pepper.
Dredge
steak in flour.
Dip in eggs, and then back in flour again.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter.
Cook broccoli and rice as directed on package.
Combine remainder of ingredients.
Stir in broccoli.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german chocolate coconut pecan topping
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, evaporated milk, beaten egg yolks and shortening.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Cool 15 minutes.
Spread only between layers and on top of cake.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Remove skin from chicken and cut chicken into 1-inch strips. Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Lightly coat chicken strips with flour mixture.
Melt butter in a frying pan over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook on both sides until browned, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve with mild salsa, meatless spaghetti sauce or plain yogurt mixed with green onions.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Dust well-greased Bundt pan with first 2 ingredients.
Mix together cake mix, pudding and poppy seed.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into prepared Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: shrimp de jonghe
directions: To melted butter, add garlic, parsley, paprika, cayenne and cooking sherry; mix well.
Add bread crumbs.
Place shrimp in a 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Spoon butter mixture over.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley before serving.

title: pear and gorgonzola salad
directions: Puree berries in blender.
Strain through a sieve to remove seeds.
Whisk the puree together with syrup, vinegar, mustard, tarragon, sugar and sour cream.
Chill.

title: layered mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck, then add seasonings and finish cooking. Put small amount picante sauce in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Line with flour shells.
Cover with refried beans and thin layer of picante sauce.
Layer shells, then ground chuck, then shells, then cheese (save shredded cheese for top) and picante sauce, then shells.
Cover with picante sauce and shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until melted and sauce is bubbling.

title: creamy salmon spread
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; blend well.
Spoon into crock or small bowl. Cover; refrigerate until firm.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone and cut or tear into small pieces.
Add soup and broth, salt and pepper (pre-mixed) to chicken and add eggs.
Toss until chicken is coated.
Pour into buttered casserole.

title: fingerpaint
directions: Thoroughly dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir constantly while cooking over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil, loses whiteness and starts to thicken.
Lower heat and continue stirring about 2 minutes until mixture is very thick and smooth. Let cool slightly.
Color by stirring in powdered or liquid tempera or food coloring.
Leftover can be stored in a covered jar in the refrigerator.

title: savory mushrooms
directions: Bring bouillon to a boil.
Add washed wild rice; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove from heat.
Saute mushroom caps in butter.
Mix rice, almonds, herbs and spices and fill mushroom caps.
Drizzle with fresh lemon juice.
Bake on cookie sheet at 300° for 15 minutes.
May easily be prepared a day prior to re-heating.

title: lemon broccoli
directions: Trim off large

leaves of broccoli and remove tough ends of lower stalks. Wash broccoli thoroughly and cut into spears. Arrange spears in a vegetable steamer over boiling water. Cook and stem for about 5 minutes or until crisp-tender. Drain. Transfer to a serving platter. Sprinkle with grated lemon rind, salt and pepper. Garnish with lemon rind curls, if desired.

title: jewish gradnies(chicken soup)
directions: Pull skin off necks, remove backs.

title: sourdough bread #3
directions: For best results, use unbleached flour.
Scald milk and stir in butter; cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add this to the basic batter from Sourdough Bread #2.
Add 2 cups flour; mix well.
Blend sugar, salt and soda; sprinkle over top of dough and stir in gently.
Cover bowl and set in warm spot.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Stir down; add remaining flour until too stiff to stir with spoon.
Turn out on floured board and knead, adding flour as required until dough is smooth and satiny.
Better too wet then dry.
Divide in half; place in greased bread pans and butter tops.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425°, then 40 minutes at 325°.

title: apple puff pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a skillet. Add brown sugar and apples; stir to coat.
Cook over medium-low heat for about 1 minute, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; set aside.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter in a 10-inch ovenproof skillet, tilting pan to coat the sides.
Whisk milk, flour, eggs and cinnamon in a medium bowl.
Pour into skillet; cook for 1 minute.
Place into oven; bake until puffed and golden, 12 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar; serve immediately.

title: barbecue chicken sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and cook over low flame for about 10 minutes. Stir.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix sugar, brown sugar, eggs, cooking oil and vanilla.
Add plain flour, baking soda, salt, nuts, dates or raisins, cornflakes, rolled oats and coconut.
Mix well and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Cook at 325° until done.

title: california seafood brunch bake
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter in skillet over low heat for 8 minutes, remove from heat.
Stir in crabmeat, green onions and cheese.
Layer bread cubes and seafood mixture, half at a time, in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, pressing down layers.
Whisk eggs and remaining ingredients in bowl.
Pour over layers.
Chill, covered, for 4 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until set.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Combine ingredients in mixer except for crust.
Beat eggs in one at a time.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Chill and serve with your favorite fruit topping.

title: savory snack mix
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix popcorn, cereal, peanuts and pretzel sticks in an ungreased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Heat margarine over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat, stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over cereal mixture and mix until well coated.
Bake 15 minutes, stirring twice.
Turn into a bowl and cool.
Store loosely covered.
Makes about 9 cups of snack, 300 calories per cup.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Crumble cake into 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 1 carton of whipped topping.
Spoon over crumbled cake. Spread strawberries over mixture.
Spread glaze over strawberries.
Top with remaining carton of whipped topping.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: macaroni and ham salad
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions; drain.
Cool. Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.
Combine cooled rotini with remaining ingredients and toss lightly.
Chill.

title: edna's punch
directions: Mix tea base, pineapple and orange juices together.
Chill in freezer for several hours until ice crystals form.
Stir every 2 - 3 hours.
When ready to serve, pour into punch bowl, add ginger ale.
May be chilled in refrigerator and served over ice.
Makes 2 1/2 - 3 gallons.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine drained pineapple with other ingredients, cutting margarine in small pieces and stirring in.
Sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers about 1/2-inch thick over mixture.
Bake in 350° oven about 40 minutes.

title: creole sauce
directions: Heat butter or oleo in saucepan.
Toss in vegetables and cook, stirring frequently, until onions are limp.
Add and stir in soup, 1/2 cup of water and drained mushrooms, pimento, parsley and salt. Cook until heated through.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Bread:
In a large bowl make a stiff batter of ingredients. Grease large bowl; put in dough, grease or Pam spray top of dough. Cover with waxed paper.
Let rise 12 hours.
Punch dough down. Divide in 3 parts.
Knead each part on floured pastry sheet a few times (8 to 10).
Put into 3 loaf pans or into rolls.
Grease pans and brush top of dough with oil.
Let rise 4 to 5 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes; rolls for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order, excluding the nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into well greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and chips over top of the batter.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine eggs, half and half, onion, salt and cayenne pepper. Blend until smooth.
Drain crabmeat on paper towels until very dry.
