Sprinkle crab, mushrooms and cheese over bottom of pie shell.
Pour in egg mixture and top with chopped parsley.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 30 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Store in airtight container.

title: onion bake fish
directions: Mix sour cream, mayo and dressing mix.
Dip both sides of fish into this sauce.
Crush onions and coat fish with crushed onions. Place in baking dish and bake at 350° until fish flakes with fork, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken, cheese and rice bake
directions: Cook chicken and rice.
In a large casserole dish, layer chicken, rice and cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until cheese melts.

title: sweet corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a square baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Bake until moist but not dry.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat, celery and onion; drain.
Add tomatoes and chillies, sauce, olives, salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes; stir occasionally.
Break up shells or chips; set aside.
Mix cheeses and egg.
Spread 1/3 of meat mixture on bottom of 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 of cheese mixture, then 1/2 of the chips.
Repeat layers, ending with meat.
Top with chips, either broken or whole.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, corn and eggs.
Pour half into 2-quart baking dish.
Add uncooked sausage evenly on top.
Put cheese evenly on top.
Add rest of cornmeal to this.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except raisins and pecans. Blend well.
Then add pecans and raisins.
Fill well-greased and floured 1 pound coffee cans to 1/2 full.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 4 cans.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Peel and mash well.
Add sugar, melted margarine, coconuts, pecans and spices.
Mix well. Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Pour mixture in dish. Top with marshmallows.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes at 250° or until marshmallows are brown.

title: layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in pan to be cooked in, approximately 12 x 8 x 2-inch.
Add graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate and butterscotch chips and nuts.
Drizzle condensed milk over top of all.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Makes approximately 24 squares.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: In a punch bowl, layer the following twice.
Makes a good colorful dessert.

title: baked celery casserole
directions: Cook celery for 8 minutes in small amount of salted water; drain.
Mix with all remaining above ingredients.
Pour into a 1-quart rectangular baking dish, buttered.

title: confetti rice
directions: In a large skillet, dry saute the onions and green pepper until tender.
Add corn, oregano, paprika, pimento and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Add rice, peas and soy sauce and heat through.
Serve hot or cold.

title: mandarin pork chops
directions: In a large skillet, brown chops in oil on both sides.
Remove from skillet.
In the skillet, add remaining ingredients, except orange segments and green pepper.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Add chops; cover and simmer for about 20 minutes or until tender.
Add orange segments and green pepper.
Simmer a few minutes until thoroughly heated.
Serves 4.

title: spicy steamed clams
directions: In a heavy saucepan, cook the garlic, pepper flakes and oregano in the oil over moderately low heat, stirring, for 1 minute.
Add the onion and fennel; cook the mixture over moderate heat, stirring, until the fennel is softened.
Add the tomatoes with the reserved juice, wine and salt and pepper to taste; simmer the mixture, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Add the clams; steam them, covered, for 5 to 7 minutes, or until they have opened.
Discard any unopened ones.

title: gingerbread on the coals
directions: Cut tops from oranges.
Remove fruit from shells.
Save for fruit salad.
Mix gingerbread mix and water.
Place batter in orange cups and carefully set cups upright in hot coals.
Cook about 12 minutes or until tops of cakes lose their sheen.
Remove from coals and cool slightly.
Top with small dab of oleo and eat with a spoon.

title: lemon cake icing
directions: Cook all ingredients, except butter, until thick in a pot on low heat.
Add butter and beat.
Makes enough icing to ice 5 thin layers of cake.
Ice first layer and beat icing.
Ice each additional layer and beat icing each time.
Allow icing to air dry on cake before covering cake.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Saute onions in butter and add tomatoes and soup.
Season with garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook noodles.
Mix all in baking dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Melt peanut butter and chips in double boiler.
Add cereal and pour in square pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: mushroom-bacon stuffing
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Crumble into bowls.
Pour off all but 1/4 cup bacon drippings.
Add melted margarine, mushrooms, celery, onion, sage, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Saute 10 minutes until veggies are tender.
Remove from heat.
Add bread crumbs, broth and vegetable mixture.
Toss well.
Spread in a large greased baking dish.
Bake 1/2 hour to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, spices and salt; let boil.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Cool; place in refrigerator.
Ready to eat in 4 days.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Cut cookie roll in 8 equal slices.
Cut each slice in fourths. Bake 8 to 9 minutes at 375°.
Immediately put a miniature peanut butter cup in middle.

title: corn soup
directions: Blend corn, milk, salt and pepper on high 4 minutes.
Add margarine and heat to desired temperature.

title: ground beef-filled squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise; remove seeds.
Place cut sides down in baking pan; add 1/4-inch boiling water to pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until almost tender.
Saute ground beef until crumbly.
Add stuffing mix, parsley, salt, onion, pepper and bouillon; toss lightly to combine.
Turn squash, cut sides up. Fill with beef mixture; return to oven and bake for 20 or 30 minutes longer.
Saute mushrooms in butter; arrange over stuffed squash.

title: lemonade
directions: Pour over ice cubes in 12 ounce glass.
Fill glass with water and serve.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in water.
Add fruit juice and chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serves 25.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Lightly butter bread slices and cut in fourths (square).
Take squares and form buttered side in small tart pans.
Fill with mixture of remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Freezes well.

title: halloween bread(a spook brings this to us)
directions: Combine and mix well the sugar, brown sugar, pumpkin, salad oil and eggs.
Sift together and add flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and ginger.
Stir in water.
Add pecans and raisins.
Mix well and spoon into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
When done, turn out on a rack to cool.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Scald milk; cool to lukewarm. Combine sugar and potatoes in a large mixing bowl; mix well. Add milk and shortening.
Stir in yeast. Sift 6 cups flour, salt, baking powder and soda. Stir into yeast mixture. Cover dough; let rise for 2 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
In a large bowl, stir together last 6 ingredients until smooth.
Add other ingredients and toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables in large bowl and toss lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients in a medium saucepan, bring to boil over low heat, stirring gently to blend and dissolved sugar.
Pour cooled vinegar mixture over vegetables, cover and chill for 24 hours. Serve and enjoy.
Serves 6-8 people.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain.
Cook beans and hambone in water slowly for three hours.
Add all ingredients except seasoned salt. Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Add seasoned salt to taste.
Serves 8.
Serve over rice.

title: homestead garden's holiday mulled cider
directions: Bring to a boil to dissolve sugar.
Simmer 15 minutes or put in crock-pot on low.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook milk and sugar until it forms a soft ball in cold water. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir well, then pour into buttered pan(s).
When cool, cut into 2-inch squares and serve.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix crushed vanilla wafers, powdered sugar and pecans.
Add melted butter and thawed orange juice. Mix well.
Roll into small balls. Roll in finely grated coconut.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
These freeze well.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks and flavoring. Roll nuts and fruit in 3/4 cup flour; mix remainder of flour in batter.
Add fruit and mixture into batter.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter (mix with hands).
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Turn out of pan when completely cool.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Cut wieners in 1-inch pieces.
Chop onion and brown in large skillet.
Add tomatoes (broken into smaller pieces) and wiener pieces.
Season with garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer until wieners plump up (5 to 7 minutes).

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients with liquid.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: scripture cake
directions: Combine as any other cake mixture.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven for approximately 1 hour.
Where different ingredients are mentioned in the same verse, use common cooking sense.
King James or Revised Standard contains the best terminology for translation of modern ingredients.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, soup, eggs, onion, mayonnaise, salt and pepper in casserole dish.
Combine melted margarine with croutons. Cover broccoli mix.
Spread cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add eggs, oil and sour cream.
Stir until blended.
Stir in corn.
Add chilies.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with 1/2 cup grated cheese. Repeat with remaining batter and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Stir yeast into warm water.
Hold aside.
Heat buttermilk, margarine, salt and sugar (works great in microwave!).
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 1 cup flour that has the soda and baking powder added.
Beat well.

title: sandy's potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and mix with crushed cornflakes.
Put mixture on top of casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Will freeze, thaw and cook.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Steam broccoli until you can pierce with fork, cut into bite-size pieces, and cover bottom of medium casserole dish. Parboil chicken, about 8 minutes.
Cut into cubes, layer on top of broccoli.
Combine mayonnaise, soup and cheese, spread over chicken.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: onion dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients and dissolve with vinegar.
Add onion juice or grated onion.
Then add salad oil slowly and blend with rotary beater.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Stew chicken; reserve broth.
Remove meat from bones.
Discard skin and chop into small pieces.
Cook celery until tender.
Add all ingredients to broth; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 5 servings.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Let cream cheese get to room temperature.
Whip together cream cheese and condensed milk.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, add pie filling to top of pie and serve.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter.
Use mixture to line a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together.
Bake until done at 350°.

title: 2-step vegetable soup
directions: Drain liquid from all vegetables except tomatoes. Combine all ingredients in large pot. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve with crackers or warm bread.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Drain fruit; mix Eagle Brand milk, Cool Whip and lemon juice. Fold fruit into mixture.
Pour into 2 graham cracker pie crusts. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: aunt mickie's fruit delight
directions: Drain juice from all the fruit and mix sour cream and coconut together.
Chill for a couple of hours before serving.

title: delicious cake
directions: Combine all ingredients with electric mixer. Pour into prepared 9 X 13 pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken divine
directions: Arrange broccoli in baking dish; place chicken on top. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter and bread crumbs and sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature.
Add sugar, salad dressing and whipped cream.
Blend all together.
Mix together cranberry sauce, well drained, crushed pineapple, marshmallows and pecans.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Place in a Pyrex dish and freeze.

title: easy pudding cake
directions: In large bowl, mix together pie filling, flour, salt, baking soda, sugar and chopped nuts.
Beat together eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add to first mixture and beat well with a spoon.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Melt butter and lightly saute onions and celery in pan.
Add to bread crumb mixture, which has been crumbled in bowl.
Add other ingredients and mix well with hands or large spoon.
Spoon into shallow pans and press.
Bake at 400° for about 20 or 25 minutes.
Serves 8.
Serve with turkey, hen or duck.

title: nigerian african stew
directions: Cut meat into small cubes and place in pot of water 2 inches above meat.
Next add all ingredients, except tomatoes, tomato paste, tomato sauce, tomato puree and spinach.
When meat is almost cooked, add tomatoes, tomato paste, puree and tomato sauce as well as spinach.
(Cooking time is approximately 1 hour.) Serve over cooked white rice.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: egg rolls
directions: Cook and drain meat. Place in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Can use 1/2 package slaw mix instead of cabbage. Mix together and follow directions on wraps to rolls.

title: pie crust
directions: In large bowl sift together flour, sugar, and salt.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until crumbly.
In a small bowl beat water, vinegar and egg.
Add to flour.
Cover bowl and chill at least 1/2 an hour before rolling.
This can be kept in the refrigerator for a week.

title: party rye pizzas(great for snacks or a party!!)
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage until done.
Drain; add seasonings.
Combine with melted Velveeta cheese and spread on party rye bread.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake on cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: carmen's crab spread
directions: Chop onions, tops and all, finely.
Add to soft cream cheese with remainder of ingredients.
Use fork to flake crab and mix well.
Can shape into a log roll in foil.
Refrigerate until firm and flavors blend.
Put in middle of platter and arrange favorite fancy crackers around when ready to serve.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Whip the cream.
Crumble in Blue cheese.
Fold cream and Blue cheese into mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Yields 2 cups.
Thin with 1 to 2 tablespoons of milk to use the next day.

title: whitney's delight
directions: Make 1 envelope of Lipton soup over medium heat.
When soup is ready, turn off and add rice.
Cook bacon and drain.
Saute celery.
Mix rice, celery and bacon in casserole dish.
Top rice with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Enjoy!

title: sausage quiche
directions: Punch holes in pie shell and bake before pouring mixture. Preheat oven to 375°.
Fully cook sausage; add cheese, onion and flour.
Beat eggs, milk and parsley flakes.
Slowly pour over sausage mixture in pie shell.
Bake on cookie sheet for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian holiday punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl. Serves 14.

title: brunch for a bunch
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until brown, stirring to crumble. Drain.
Place hash browns in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Layer with sausage, cheese and green peppers.
Combine eggs and milk, stirring well.
Pour over green peppers.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in 8 1/2 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 2 cups flour.
Add shortening and ice water.
May need to add a little flour.
Roll on floured surface very thin.
Cut into strips about 1 x 3-inches. Cut up chicken and add to 1 quart of water.
Add salt and pepper and half an onion.
Boil until done (if you like, you may debone chicken, but not necessary).
Lay dumplings on top of broth very gently.
Simmer slowly.
Move them around with a fork in the juice.
Heat milk and pour into pot slowly.
Cook approximately 45 minutes or until dumplings are done.

title: marinated veggies
directions: Add any type of vegetables that you like; let it set for 24 hours.
You can continue to add veggies as they are eaten.
Will keep about 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: chicken perlo
directions: Boil chicken and sausage.
Add spices together until tender. Debone chicken.
Cut sausage and chicken into small pieces.
Mix rice with broth.
Put ingredients together and bring to a boil. Cut on low heat, cover tightly, 20 minutes.
Then cut burner off and wait until rice has softened, about 15 minutes.

title: snowball salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover tightly and freeze.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving.
Can be used as salad or dessert.

title: cabbage salad
directions: In a small bowl, mix together oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and chicken flavor packet from Ramen noodles and set aside. Chop head of cabbage and slice onions.
Put in a large bowl. Crush Ramen noodles and add to cabbage.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Place 6 slices of toast in an oblong pan.
Mix together tuna, onion, mayonnaise and noodles.
Spread over toast in dish.
Cover with slices of American cheese.
Put rest of toast (6) on top. Mix soup, milk and salt; pour onto center of toast within 2 inches of sides.
Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: the scripture cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together to create divine fruitcake.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Bake in 10 x 4-inch tube pan.

title: anise christmas cookies
directions: This eye-catching and mouth-watering treat uses a mix of several sliced fruits (except apples) such as plums, kiwi, bananas, strawberries, etc., and/or whole small berries or cherries, grapes, etc.
The fruits are not cooked.

title: appetizer pastry(tart shell)
directions: Cut chilled butter into 1/2-inch slices.
In a medium bowl, combine flour and salt.
Use a pastry blender to cut in butter slices until mixture resembles oatmeal; set aside.

title: parsley-basil clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic in butter and oil 3 minutes or until soft.
Stir in clams and liquid clam juice, parsley, basil and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon clam sauce over hot spaghetti or linguini. Makes 3 cups.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add the water and lemon juice.
Over high heat, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened and clear (4 to 5 minutes).
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour into baked shell. Chill 4 to 6
hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pam's bars
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Add eggs.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Remove.
Top with chips.
Pour milk over; sprinkle with coconut.
Bake for 20 minutes more.
Melt 1/2 cup chocolate chips and shortening.
Drizzle over top.

title: prime rib roast
directions: Pat optional ingredients into meat.
Place roast, fat side up, in baking pan.
Add water.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Do not open oven door.
You can do this in the morning.
Then, before serving, cook at 375° for 30 minutes rare, 45 minutes for medium or 1 hour for well done.
Cook uncovered.
Serves 6.

title: party mix
directions: Combine cereal, crackers, pretzels, dressing and dill weed; stir well.
Sprinkle oil over it and stir well.
Pour in paper bag and let sit for 2 hours, shaking occasionally.

title: crab meat appetizers
directions: Spread cream cheese on 9-inch dinner plate.
Add cocktail sauce on top and sprinkle crab meat on top.
Chill.
Spread on crackers.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, and make balls.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain 1 jar artichoke hearts and use juice to saute onion and garlic.
Chop hearts and add to sauteed mixture.
Beat eggs in bowl; add bread crumbs, salt, pepper, oregano, Tabasco sauce and parsley.
Add sauteed mixture.
Mix well and add cheese.
Bake at 325° in a 7 x 11-inch baking dish for 30 minutes.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Bake at 400° for about 35 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook zucchini 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in jello.
After jello is dissolved, pour into jars and seal or put in freezer.

title: creamy hash browns(crock-pot)
directions: Place potatoes in an ungreased 5-quart slow cooker. In a bowl, combine the remaining ingredients. Pour over potatoes and mix well. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours or until potatoes are tender and heated through. Yield: 14 servings.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add the rest of the ingredients; mix well and pour into a lightly greased mold.

title: tiramisu(sugar-free)
directions: Pour 1/2 cup of milk into blender container.
Add cream cheese; cover.
Blend until smooth.
Blend in the remaining 1 cup milk.
Dissolve coffee in water; add to blender with brandy.
Add pudding mix; cover.
Blend until smooth, scraping down sides. Pour into large bowl.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Cut ladyfingers in half crosswise.
Cover bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers halves.
Place remaining halves, cut ends down, around sides of pan.
Spoon pudding mixture into pan.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Remove side of pan.
Sprinkle with grated chocolate.
Serves 12.

title: pretzels dipped in dark or white chocolate
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water in a double boiler.
Dip pretzels until fully covered.
Let excess chocolate drip back into pot.
Cool on waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator or freezer. Makes about 40.

title: miniature fruit strawberries
directions: In blender grind nuts and coconut.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours to harden.
Mold into strawberry.
Shape by hand.
Roll in fine red sugar.
Dip ends in green sugar to form stems, or small pieces of almonds dyed green can be stuck on end as stem.
Use 2 per strawberry.
Yields 50 or more.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator or can be frozen.

title: cherry chip cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into tube pan lined with wax paper.
Cook for approximately 1 hour at 350°.
Leave in pan.
Cool a little.
Punch full of holes with fork.

title: homemade dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat eggs in large mixing bowl. Add sugar, yeast and oil.
Mix well.
Add 6 cups of flour, salt and scalded milk alternately.
Beat until satiny looking.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Turn onto bread board with 2 cups flour and knead.
Roll and cut into biscuits.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: new zealand panlova
directions: Beat egg whites, water and salt until stiff.
Add 3/4 cup of sugar and beat again.
Into remaining 1/4 cup of sugar add cornstarch.
Add this to egg mixture and beat some more.
Keep beating until mixture looks marshmallowy, then add vanilla and beat into mixture.
Spray Pam on baking sheet.
Cut a piece of waxed paper to fit and place in baking sheet.
Spray waxed paper with Pam.
Pour egg white mixture on the waxed paper.
Put in oven at ???° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to ???° and bake for 1 hour.
Do not open oven door.
Turn off heat and allow to set for 1/2 hour.

title: tropical fruit ice cream
directions: *Or can use fresh medium sized soursop (extract with 1 1/2 cups water; 3 or 4 large mangos (blend pulp); or 2 large coconuts (extract with 2 cups water in blender).

title: zesty cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese.
Add olives and remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Cover bowl and chill thoroughly.
Shape chilled mixture into ball. Roll in parsley or nuts.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Presweeten fruit with 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup flour.
Put in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Use an 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Toss, chill and serve.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine crumbs and 1/2 cup butter, melted.
Press in 9 x 13 pan.
Chill.
In small mixing bowl, combine eggs, 1/2 cup butter and powdered sugar.
Beat on high speed about 5 minutes until thick and creamy.
Spread on chilled crust.
Arrange sliced bananas, slightly overlapping, to cover creamed mixture.
Spread well drained pineapple over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Cover and refrigerate 10 to 12 hours.

title: butter pecan dessert
directions: Crush Ritz crackers. Melt butter and mix with crumbs in a 13 x 9 pan.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts thoroughly.
Form into ball. Place in refrigerator to chill and become firm.
Take out and roll in pecans.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Cut margarine into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk and stir until dough clings together. Knead dough 10 to 12 strokes on lightly floured surface.
Roll out to a 16 x 12-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle sausage evenly atop dough. Roll up (jelly roll) style, starting from long side.
Slice into 1-inch slices.
Place cut side down on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 450°
for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate drops(soft cookies)
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk alternately with dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Add cocoa and mix well.
Add vanilla, maple flavoring and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased pans.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cook 5 minutes and cool the first 3 ingredients.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients - add to sugar mixture.
Mix well, then add raisin mixture and stir. Drop on greased baking sheet and bake for 9-10 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed, but in 3 cake pans.
Stir 3/4 cup sugar and crushed pineapple together.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, mix sour cream and 1 3/4 cup sugar until blended.
Add Cool Whip and set aside.
When cake layers are cool, spoon pineapple mixture over each layer, letting juice soak into cake.
Top with sour cream mixture.
Continue with each layer.

title: salami
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and mix thoroughly with your hand.
Shape into 3 (10-inch) logs.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerator for 24 hours.
This step is mandatory.

title: easy italian pasta casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix in casserole with chopped onion and spaghetti sauce.
Top with Cashew Cheese and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans.
Add salt.
Add water and soak overnight.
Drain the beans.
Add 2 quarts of water and ham hocks.
Bring to a boil. Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add onion, tomatoes, chili powder, lemon juice, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Simmer another 30 minutes.

title: lemon vinaigrette
directions: Puree lemon juice and garlic in food processor.
With machine running, gradually add olive oil and blend until smooth.
Add Parmesan cheese, blend until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cover the bottom of 2-quart deep pie dish or casserole with pie crust.
Cover sides also if you wish more crust.
Place peaches in mixing bowl.
Mix sugar and flour. Add water and mix well.
Pour over peaches.
Mix lightly and pour into pie dish.
Sprinkle a bit of cinnamon and nutmeg over top of peaches and dot with butter.
Make a lattice of pie crust across top of pan and bake 10 minutes.
Now cool oven to 350° and bake about 40 minutes longer.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except nuts.
Spread nuts in unbaked pie shells and divide batter between pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hello dollies
directions: Crumble graham crackers.
Mix with all ingredients.
Spoon tablespoons of batter onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: butter crust
directions: Mix flour and
salt
in
pie
pan.
Add milk and butter mixture.
Work out to sides of pan with fingers.
Bake at 350° until brown.
This is good for cream pies.

title: scuppernong pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, flour and butter to eggs and beat until well mixed.
Stir in grapes and sugar in which they were canned.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with top crust, also.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 375° and continue baking for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Very good and low-fat!

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Snip dates, figs and marshmallows with scissors.
When scissors get sticky, dip them in powdered sugar.
Add nuts, salt and cherries.
Mix in 1 1/2 cups cracker crumbs.
Add cream and mix well.
Line a deep 9-inch round pan with waxed paper.
Shape mixture into a round cake and coat with remaining crumbs.
Press firmly into pan; cover with waxed paper.
Chill overnight.
Turn out and pull off waxed paper.

title: seafoam lime mold
directions: Dissolve lime jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and lemon juice.
Gradually add to cream cheese and blend.
Chill until almost firm.
Fold in marshmallows, pineapple and nuts. Pour into one-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Place in casserole baking dish.
Add mushroom soup.
Crush enough Ritz crackers over top to cover.
Pour over crackers the melted butter (may use less).
Top with cheese slices or Cheez Whiz.
Place in moderate oven until cheese melts.

title: cappuccino coffee mix
directions: Mix together.
To serve, use 2 teaspoons mix to a cup of boiling water.
Excellent gift.

title: un-apple pie
directions: Peel and seed zucchini.
Cut into lengthwise strips and slice like you would an apple.
Cover with water and boil two minutes. Drain and set aside to cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together and stir gently through zucchini.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust and cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Lower heat to 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Tastes just like an apple pie!

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in separate bowl.
Mix all ingredients and put in greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: banana cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9x13x2 inch baking pan that has been greased and lightly floured on bottom only.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of cake.
As soon as cake comes from oven, add topping and broil as directed.

title: glazed acorn squash
directions: Place squash in shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over squash; cover.
Bake in a 350! oven for 30 minutes until almost tender.
Baste several times with pan juices during baking.
Uncover; baste.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes longer until squash is tender.

title: dirt pie
directions: Grind cookies fine.
Mix all other ingredients.
Beat with mixer until thick.

title: golden shrimp rice
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine until tender.
Add shrimp and cook until shrimp turns pink.
Add rice, water, salt and pepper to taste.
When it comes to a boil, turn to simmer.
Cover and cook until rice is done, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple streusel muffins
directions: Prepare muffin mix according to package directions; fold in apple. Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full. In a small bowl, combine the walnuts, flour, brown sugar and butter; sprinkle over batter.

title: oreo trifle
directions: Crumble Oreos until they are like potting soil. Cream margarine, cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla. Mix pudding and milk. Mix pudding mixture with cream cheese mixture. When thick, fold in Cool Whip. Layer in trifle bowl, cookies first, then filling, until there are 4 layers of cookie and 3 layers of filling. Refrigerate 4 hours. Can be frozen.

title: marinated pork party sandwiches
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; cover and chill at least 8 hours.(Mayonnaise mixture)
Trim fat from tenderloins.
Place tenderloins in a large heavy-duty, zip-top plastic bag.
Combine oil and next 6 ingredients; pour over tenderloins.
Seal bag; marinate in refrigerator 8 hours, turning bag occasionally.
Remove tenderloins from marinade, reserving marinade.
Place tenderloins on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer into thickest portion of 1 tenderloin.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 30 minutes or until meat thermometer registers 160°, basting occasionally with marinade. Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut tenderloins into 1/4 inch slices and arrange on a serving platter lined with kale leaves, if desired. Serve with mayonnaise mixture and cocktail rolls.

title: chicken in golden sauce
directions: Combine flour, pepper and salt.
Dust chicken with mixture and in a single layer, skin side down, lay in buttered dish, 12 x 18 x 2-inch.
Drizzle margarine over chicken.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Turn and bake 20 more minutes.
Stir soup and pour over chicken.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Delicious!

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; stir well.
Make a well in the middle and add all other ingredients except pecans and vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: parisian onion soup
directions: Simmer thinly sliced onions in water until tender.
Dissolve bouillon.
Add to onions.
Simmer a few minutes.
Place a few croutons and a slice of toast in each bowl.
Add a slice of cheese.
Pour soup over cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Let stand for a minute or two to melt cheese.

title: bagels
directions: Combine the yeast and 1 3/4 cups flour.
Add water, sugar and salt to yeast mixture.
Beat at a low speed for 1/2 minute, constantly scraping the sides of the bowl.
Then beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Turn onto a lightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Cover and let rest for 15 minutes.
Divide dough into 12 portions.
Shape into balls and punch a hole in center of each with a floured finger.
Pull gently to enlarge hole. Keep in uniform shape.
Cover and let rise for 20 minutes.

title: preacher dan's mega peanut butter chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small bowl, combine flour, salt, baking soda; set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter, brown sugar, white sugar, vanilla and egg until creamy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in oats, pecans and peanut butter chips. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets, any size you prefer (the bigger, the better).

title: quickest peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan that you cook the cobbler. Mix together the cake mix and milk. Pour the batter in the middle of pan with the melted butter (don't spread the batter). Now pour 1 can peaches and juice on top of batter and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar. Cook in 325° oven. Do not boil cobbler, remove when top is gloden brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put into casserole dish.
Add topping.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with orange juice.
Combine sugar, flour, spices and salt.
Cut in butter with 2 knives or a pastry blender to form crumbs.
(Batter will be quite stiff, makes nice large firm crumbs).
Put crumbs over apples.
Bake at 375° approximately 45 minutes.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix flour, milk and oil with fork until makes soft dough. Pat out on floured surface.
Make into biscuits.
(Makes about 4 large ones.)
Bake at 450° on greased cake pan about 20 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer each of the vegetables in a bowl.
Mix Miracle Whip and sugar together and spread on top of vegetables.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate, covered, and add tomatoes before serving.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 15-inch casserole.
Top with cheese.
Mix soup and water and spread over top.
Top with bread crumbs.
Pour melted butter over bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bacon and egg casserole
directions: Fry bacon.
Remove from skillet.
Drain fat, leaving enough to fry onions until soft.
Add soup, milk and sliced hard-boiled eggs.
Mix all together.
Stir in cheese and crumble bacon on top. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: road runner cake(this makes good shortcake.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (9-inch) layer pans.
Sift together in a large bowl flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. Mix well.
Add shortening and 1/2 of the milk.
Beat for 2 minutes; add remaining milk, vanilla and eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes, then pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake for 25 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes and put on cooling rack.

title: margaret's do-nuts("dee - licious!")
directions: Dissolve the baking soda in the sour cream and set aside. Beat together the eggs, sugar and oil or melted shortening.
Make sure it is well beaten.
Add the sour cream with the soda in it, the pinch of salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Stir well and add 1/2 cup flour and the buttermilk.
Stir well.
Put the baking powder in 1 cup flour and stir into the mixture.
Keep adding flour, until dough feels ready to roll, cut.
Helps to chill in the refrigerator before rolling it out to cut.

title: crazy cake
directions: Place all dry ingredients into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Stir to mix up.
Add wet ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: jean tucker's peanut butter ice cream
directions: Blend well.
Finish filling freezer with milk.
Mix well and freeze.
For chocolate peanut butter ice cream; use chocolate milk.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger meat; drain.
Add taco seasoning and 3/4 cup water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Let cool.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough in large back pan, and bake as directed.
Allow to cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and soup mix and spread evenly over cooled crust.
Add diced vegetables.

title: carolyn koch's fudge
directions: Mix all together.
Cook until it comes to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes longer.
Take off heat.
Then add:

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat all ingredients for 7 minutes.
Bake for 1 hour for large greased loaf pan.
Less time for smaller pans.

title: oatmeal chip bars
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well with mixer at medium speed.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in oats, chips and pecans.
Spread mixture into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: two flavor fudge
directions: Combine in pan the brown sugar, white sugar, milk and oleo and bring to a rolling boil, stirring frequently.
Boil for 15 minutes stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream, butterscotch and chocolate chips.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Blend in nuts and vanilla.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter; add sugar and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating to blend after each addition and again until light and fluffy. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating continuously.
Blend in sour cream.
Add flavoring, one teaspoon at a time, and blend well.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours (or longer).

title: parmesan cauliflower
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets.
Cook in small amount of boiling salted water until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese and Blue cheese to soften at room temperature.
Add garlic salt; mix well.
Place in aluminum foil; shape into ball.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Serve on cheese board with assorted crackers.

title: fried plantains
directions: Peel the plantains; cut them into thin, round slices.
Dip into salty seasoned cold water; place in strainer to drain off excess water.
Fry in vegetable oil until golden brown; place on paper towel to absorb excessive oil.
Sprinkle with a little all season.
Place on a serving platter to cool.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix together with mixer cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, red pepper and garlic powder and pour into 9-inch pie dish.
Top with the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers.
In large pan combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring.
Boil 8 to 10 minutes or until thickened, stirring frequently.
Immediately fill hot pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Place lids on jars. Process in boiling water canner for 15 minutes.
Yields 3 pints.

title: sweet potato crisp
directions: Cook sweet potatoes; peel and slice crosswise, about 3/8 inch thick.
Spread in a buttered, large but shallow baking-serving dish.
Cut butter into flour and brown sugar.
Add pepper, cream and nuts; mix well.
Sprinkle over potato slices.

title: macaroni salad(club member: kristi mayfield)
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set overnight.

title: party mix
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter.
Add Worcestershire sauce and stir until blended.

title: crab quiche
directions: In blender, combine mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch. Process until smooth.
Add crab meat, cheese and onion and blend at low speed just to combine (3 to 4 seconds).
Pour mixture into baked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until top is puffed up and golden brown.
Remove from oven and allow to rest 10 minutes before serving to firm up the custard.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange in a greased dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and sour cream together.
Add cheese, bread crumbs and butter.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix well and bake in a 9 x 13 pan that has been greased well and wax paper added to bottom.
Cook at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: easy cranberry salad("yum-yum")
directions: Grind cranberries and apples; add marshmallows and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Mix well; let stand.
Beat cream; add nuts to cream.
Mix with the rest of ingredients.
Freeze in serving size containers until ready to serve.

title: sunday brunch casserole
directions: Remove and discard crusts from bread if desired.
Butter bread. Cube and place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese, sausage, red pepper and onions in order over the bread.

title: spinach stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells.
Fill with spinach souffle.
Make a cheese sauce with the last 4 ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper as it cooks.
Stir constantly until cheese melts.
Pour over shells. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pork chop and potato bake
directions: Brown chops, sprinkle with salt, set aside. Combine soup, milk, sour cream potatoes, 1/2 C cheese and 1/2 C chopped onion. Spoon mixture into 9x13 baking dish. Arrange chops over potatoes. Bake covered at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions and bake uncovered for 5 minutes longer.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to cream mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into 3 greased 9-inch pans and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over corn mixture; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: shrimp luncheon dish
directions: Mix all ingredients and cover.
When steaming, turn to low and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: rosemary potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F.
Lightly oil baking pan.
Cut a narrow wedge 2/3 through each potato.
Insert a rosemary sprig and a sliver or two of garlic in each wedge.
Drizzle a bit of olive oil in the opening, too.
Place potatoes in baking dish, making sure none of them touch.

title: green bean bake with onion
directions: Cook frozen beans according to package directions; drain (or drained canned beans).
Combine the cooked frozen or the canned beans, mushroom soup, pimiento and lemon juice.
Turn mixture into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 35 minutes. Sprinkle with French fried onions.
Continue baking, uncovered, until onions are heated through about 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: collard greens
directions: Check leaves of collards carefully; remove pulpy stems and discolored spots on leaves. Wash leaves thoroughly; drain well and chop. Combine collards, water and salt in a Dutch oven. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low. Simmer, uncovered, for 25 minutes or until tender. Drain well. Saute salt pork in a skillet until golden brown; do not drain. Add collards, stirring lightly. Cook over low heat 5 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chess cake
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, sugar, flour and eggs together.
Pour melted margarine over mixture; add vanilla and mix well.
Pour back into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Cut crust off bread.
Spread butter on one side of bread. Place buttered side down in greased baking dish.
Brown sausage; drain.
Sprinkle sausage on top of bread.
Sprinkle cheese on top of sausage.
Mix eggs and half and half.
Pour over bread and sausage.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Bake next morning 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 people.

title: quick caramel icing
directions: Cook, stirring, until sugar is dissolved, then cool, without stirring, until mixture forms a soft ball.
(Drop small amount in cold water to check.)
Cool to lukewarm.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 3 (7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/4-inch) loaf pans.
In bowl, beat sugar, eggs and oil until blended and light and fluffy.
Beat in pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients.
At low speed, beat dry mixture into pumpkin mixture.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cream margarine, eggs and sweetener.
Add soda, spices, flour and applesauce (or mashed bananas).
Mix well.
Fold in fruit and nuts.

title: oooey gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and 1 stick margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla and 2 eggs.
Spread on first mixture.
Sprinkle with pecans that have been rolled in small amount of powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scotch chocolate cake
directions: Bring butter, cocoa, oil and water to a boil.
Add to flour and sugar, the salt, soda and buttermilk.
Add hot mixture to this mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Have frosting made when cake comes out of the oven.
Pour over hot cake.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Add onion, bell pepper, banana pepper, red pepper, salt, pepper and garlic.
Sprinkle with flour and mix until coated.
Boil water, then add chili powder to boiling water.
Pour into meat mixture and cook on low for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Put into crock-pot and add Ro-Tel tomatoes, tomato sauce, soup and both beans.
Cook on low for 1 hour, then add halved jalapenos.
Cook for 4 hours on low.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease 2 pie plates. Rinse broccoli under cold water to thaw. Drain thoroughly. Mix broccoli, 2 cups of the cheese and onion; divide, pour into pie plates. Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper until smooth. Pour into plates. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Top with remaining cheese. Bake 1 to 2 minutes longer.

title: chocolate chunk brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts, if desired, and chocolate treasures or chunks.
Spread into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely; cut into bars.

title: beef and pepper rice skillet
directions: Brown beef in oil.

Stir in onion, rice, beef broth, one soup can of water and soy sauce. Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and cook over low heat until liquid is absorbed, about 25 minutes. Stir in green pepper and pimientos.
Heat.

title: baked apricots
directions: In greased 1 1/2 quart casserole, layer apricots, sugar and crumbs until all ingredients are used.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: party chicken
directions: Rinse dried beef in cold water.
Place beef on the bottom of 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Wrap each piece of chicken in slice of bacon.
Lay this over dried beef.
Sprinkle small amount of rosemary over.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken. Bake 3 hours, uncovered, in 275° oven.

title: coke salad
directions: Bring water to a boil with sugar and juice from cherries.
Add jello and cherries.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes and add pineapple, Coke and nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: *chicken mandalay
directions: Cut chicken into chunks or slices.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Saute chicken until golden brown; set aside.
Combine consomme, curry powder, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Drain oranges, reserving syrup. Combine syrup, lemon juice and cornstarch.
Cook, stirring, until thickened and clear.
Add dates and green pepper; simmer for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in orange sections.
Combine orange sauce with chicken mixture.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer lettuce, cauliflower, bacon bits and onions.
Make a dressing of mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and sugar.
Cover the top with the mayonnaise dressing.
When ready, sprinkle with bacon bits and mix.
Best if refrigerated 2 to 3 hours.

title: noodle soup
directions: *Use 4 medium potatoes, 1/4 head cabbage, 4 medium carrots, 1/2 red or yellow pepper (sweet), 1 large onion, scored, 1 whole tomato, 1 celery heart, 2 parsley roots, 6 pieces of top parsley and 1/2 kohlrabi.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts on a large micro-safe platter, placing meatier parts toward outer edge of platter.
Cover with plastic wrap and micro-cook 6 to 8 minutes per pound, turning pieces over midway through cooking.
If juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a fork, chicken is cooked.
Cover with plastic wrap and let stand 5 minutes.
When cool, remove skin and chunk chicken, saving broth.
Place 1/4 cup reserved broth in a 9 x 13-inch micro-safe shallow casserole.
Layer tortillas over broth and scatter chicken chunks over tortillas.
Combine the soups, half and half, onion, salsa, drained olives and 1/2 cup of the grated Cheddar.
Spread over chicken layer and micro-cook, covered with plastic wrap, on High power 12 to 14 minutes or until bubbly and hot.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese; cover with plastic wrap and let stand 3 to 5 minutes before serving.

title: mexican chicken lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain; then set aside.
While noodles are cooking, stir together egg whites, cottage cheese, parsley and chili peppers in a medium bowl; set aside.

title: milk punch(enough for approximately 25 people)
directions: Beat softened ice cream in large mixer bowl, gradually adding fruit juices, then milk.
Beat until frothy.
Pour into chilled bowl.
Great for parties and showers.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: You may omit the butterscotch or caramel chips, but use double of the other chip.

title: cheerios squares
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and butter to a boil.
Remove; add peanut butter.
Combine Cheerios, corn flakes and peanuts in a bowl. Pour boiled mixture over cereals and mix well.
Pour into buttered pan and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: tomato creme bisque
directions: In saucepan, blend soup and sour cream.
Gradually stir in water.
Heat and stir.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: tanya's treat(low calorie)
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine until crumbly.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill 15 minutes. Beat cream cheese. Add 1/4 cup sugar.
Gradually add milk and beat. Fold in whipped topping. Spread over crust.
Place peach slices on top. Dissolve jello in hot water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to jello.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Remove unmelted ice. Gently smooth over peaches.
Chill 3 hours.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: holiday hot nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, toss nuts with oil. In a small bowl, combine all spices except salt.
Add the spices to nuts, tossing nuts to cover evenly with spices.
Spread the nuts on a baking sheet in a single layer.
Bake for 10 minutes. If desired, sprinkle with salt.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, saute onion, celery and broccoli in butter for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese, soup and milk until smooth.
Place rice in a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture over, do not stir.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil in small saucepan the oleo, water and cocoa. Mix the vinegar-milk mixture with remaining ingredients.
Pour oleo mixture into bowl of flour and sugar.
Add eggs, milk mixture and vanilla.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet (approximately 10 x 15-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: pecan brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. In a large bowl beat sugars and 1/2 cup margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Blend well.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Spread in pan and bake for 23 to 28 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean. (I bake for only 13 minutes.
They burn easily.)
Cool completely. Frost.
Arrange pecan halves over frosting, if desired. Cut into 36 bars.

title: doris carson's cornbread stuffing
directions: Start with 2 packages of cornbread mix.
Crumble together all ingredients, except eggs and mushrooms.
Add the eggs and mushrooms.
Mix together; add chicken broth until runny.
Grease a baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: almond cream filling
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cold milk.
Add to hot milk in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat; cool to lukewarm.
Cream 1/2 cup butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Add to cooled cooked mixture. Brown almonds in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add to filling.
Chill until firm enough to spread on cake or chiffon roll.
Yields 12 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon together.
Cut biscuits into fourths and roll in sugar mixture.
Place in greased Bundt pan.
Put butter, 1 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon in saucepan and bring to boil.
After bringing to boil, add nuts and pour over biscuits in Bundt pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Place Jell-O into large mixing bowl.
Dissolve with only 1 cup of boiling water.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.
Be sure to leave the liquid in the strawberries and pineapple.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole #1
directions: Combine chicken, soups, sour cream and dumplings.
Place chicken mixture in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with Pepperidge Farm herb stuffing mix.
Melt the margarine; pour over top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, or until heated through.

title: fudge
directions: Microwave milk and white chocolate chips with condensed milk for 2 1/2 minutes. Stir. Microwave for another 2 1/2 minutes. Stir marshmallow cream into chocolate mixture. Stir in vanilla and pecans. Pour into buttered dish. Cut when cool.

title: ham finger sandwiches
directions: Melt margarine with chopped onion. Add poppy seed and mustard. Mix and pour on top of rolls.
Spread evenly.
Lay 3 slices of ham and cheese on top and put top rolls on.
Cover with foil and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffing balls
directions: Saute celery, onions and seasonings in the margarine in skillet, about 5 minutes.
Add to remaining ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 12 balls.
Place in well-greased muffin pan sections.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Simmer the above ingredients for 1 hour.
Melt 1 (8 ounce) package Kraft Old English cheese.
Boil 1 (8 ounce) package wide noodles and drain.
Mix all together.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix together all ingredients and enjoy with your favorite breads and crackers.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Place Twinkies on bottom of large baking dish.
Mix vanilla pudding mix with milk.
Pour over Twinkies.
Pour pineapple on and layer sliced bananas over pudding.
Pour Cool Whip on top with crushed nuts on top of that.

title: chicken scallop
directions: Combine ingredients and place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry wink cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add rest of ingredients except corn flakes.
Roll in corn flake crumbs formed into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Top each with 1/4 maraschino cherry.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mmm mmm chicken
directions: Clean and place chicken pieces in an aluminum foil-lined baking dish.
Lightly butter top sides of chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon undiluted cream of mushroom soup over chicken covering chicken completely.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top of all.
Seal aluminum foil tightly and bake at 350° until chicken is thoroughly cooked.
Uncover and bake until coating is lightly browned and crispy.

title: crock-pot roast beef
directions: Dissolve bouillon in boiling water.
Pour over beef in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with onion powder.
Cook 15 minutes on high or 8 hours on low.

title: french dip burgers
directions: In large pot, prepare gravy mix using 2 cups water.
Throw onion rings in; let cook on medium heat (rings will separate). While gravy mix is cooking, make patties.
Keep them relatively small, not size hamburger you would make for the grill.
Brown off all the patties.
If gravy mix is boiling, reduce heat.
When all patties are browned and drained from excess grease, put them all in the gravy mix, stirring them around to get covered.
Let them simmer, covered, about 1/2 hour.
Great on bun; cover with some of the onion, gravy and mustard.

title: bean dip
directions: In a saucepan, blend chili and cream cheese.
After cream cheese is melted in chili, pour into glass bowl.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spicy pickles
directions: Peel and split garlic cloves.
Empty juice out of pickle jar. Slice pickles into thin slices.
Using the pickle jar, layer ingredients as follows:

title: aunt rachel's fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, fruit cocktail and flour.
Mix well and pour into a sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. (Cooking time will vary with ovens and size and type of pan used.)

title: crisp cheese wafers
directions: In large mixing bowl, toss together cheese, flour, cereal, salt and cayenne pepper.
Mix well.
Melt butter.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over flour mixture and stir well. (Mixture will be coarse.)
Shape into 3/4-inch firm balls.
Place on lightly buttered baking sheet and bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from sheet.
Press with fork in crisscross pattern.
Yields 126 wafers.

title: lemon butter bars
directions: Lightly coat a 9 inch baking pan with cooking spray. For the crust, combine the flour and 1/4 c. sugar and blend together. Add 1/2 c. (1 stick) butter. Cut into flour-sugar mixture until it is finely mixed and the butter disappears. This will be like crumbs. Pour the crumbs into the prepared pan and smooth. Don't pat the crumbs too tightly. Bake on the middle rack of a preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until the edges are just beginning to brown.

title: moist banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, bananas, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well and pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for about 70 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add vanilla, vinegar and corn meal.
Mix and pour into 2 (10-inch) unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 275° or 300° for about 1 hour or until firm in center.

title: broccoli brunch pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inches.
Spread broccoli in plate.
Beat sour cream, cottage cheese, baking mix, butter and eggs until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Top with tomato and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites, vanilla and sugar until soft peaks form. Fold in coconut and peanut butter, which has been melted and cooled.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips in saucepan over low heat stirring constantly. Stir in nuts and noodles.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper to set.

title: hot cheese hors d'oeuvres
directions: Grind together cheese, bacon, onion and garlic.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard.
Mix well.
Spread on bread.
Broil for 6 to 7 minutes about 5 inches from broiler heat.
These can be frozen.
When ready to use, take out of freezer about half hour before needed and broil 6 to 7 minutes or until done.

title: twila's no bake cookies
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Stir and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Chill and enjoy.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with flour and nuts.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Blend Cool Whip, sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over crust.
Top with blueberry filling.
Chill until serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Beat with jam until smooth.
Shape into a ball.
Freeze for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, toast almonds and coconut in oven set at 425°.
Watch closely.
Roll ball in the browned mixture.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: gypsy stew
directions: Add cheese, mushroom soup, olives, pimentos, salt, pepper and chili powder to beef.
Heat on low fire until cheese is melted; do not burn.
Serve on slice of toast.

title: scallop chowder
directions: Saute celery and onions slowly in melted butter until onions are transparent.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper, Sauterne wine and water.
Bring to boil, then add imitation seafood.
Bring back to boil and then cut heat; simmer until potatoes are soft.
Heat whipping cream to a rolling boil in a separate pan.
Add to chowder and add parsley.

title: sour cream salad dressing
directions: Mix fruit juices, salt and sugar.
Add cream, stir until smooth.
Makes about 3/4 cup.

title: country steak
directions: Cut meat into serving sizes.
Brown meat in frying pan, using 2 tablespoons shortening.
Pour off fat.
Stir in soup and water; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Stir often.

title: cheese and onion cornbread
directions: In medium bowl, combine 1 egg, muffin mix, cheese, milk and onions.
Stir until moistened.
Turn into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chocolate fudge upside-down cake
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar, margarine, milk, flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa (1 1/2 tablespoons) together and put in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Mix together pecans, 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Sprinkle over unbaked cake mixture. Boil 1 1/4 cups water. Pour over the whole thing.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cut cored, pared apples in 1/2 inch rings or slices and cook until tender in syrup of 2 cups sugar, 1 cup water, 1/3 cup red cinnamon candies and a few drops of red food coloring.
This is a good garnish for meat, especially beef.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Stir together butter and cookie crumbs.
Press into 9-inch pie plate.
Set aside.

title: tailgate beans
directions: In a skillet, cook beef and bacon until lightly browned.
Pour off excess fat.
Combine meats with all ingredients.
Turn into casserole dish.
Heat in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: chocolate rum angel
directions: Blend first four ingredients in top of double boiler and cook over simmering water, stirring until mixture is of custard consistency and coats a spoon about 10 to 15 minutes.
Soften gelatin in cold water and add to hot custard, stirring to dissolve.
Remove 1 cup of custard and add to chocolate chips. Still until chocolate is melted.
Set aside.
When remaining custard is cool, add rum or flavoring and chill until mixture just begins to thicken.
Whip cream and fold into chilled custard. Pour mixture into a 9-inch spring-form pan or 9 x 13-inch pan. Drizzle chocolate custard over top and sprinkle with almonds. Chill to set.
If using spring-form pan, unmold.
Cut into servings and garnish each with sweetened whipped cream and a strawberry.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Boil 8 potatoes until tender.
Cool, peel and chop.
Add one diced onion, bacon crisps, olive slices and Velveeta cheese.
Add Miracle Whip and stir all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add milk gradually.
Stir in beaten egg yolks and butter.
Cook until thickened.
Add vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: pecan crunchies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, flour, soda and pecans.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cow patties
directions: Brown meats and spices; drain grease.
Add Velveeta, which has been chunked up.
(You can use Mexican flavor Velveeta if you like it spicier.)

title: cherry cheese tarts
directions: Let cream cheese and 1/2 cup butter soften to room temperature.
Mix 1/2 cream cheese, flour and butter; chill. Press dough evenly against bottom and sides of small muffin tins.

title: sugar-free lemon pie
directions: Mix vanilla pudding, skim milk, lemonade and Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.

title: simple salsa
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 1 1/2-2 hours until thick.
Put into hot jars and seal with tops.

title: helen's pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, and baking powder and set aside. Gradually blend flour mixture with milk mixture. If batter is too thick, add a little more milk. Fry in pan with canola oil.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in water with onions - or saute onions and add later.
When potatoes are cooked, add rest of ingredients and heat.
For color, you may add cooked diced carrots and also a chicken bouillon cube for more flavor.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Heat milk, salt and sugar to moderate temperature.
Add corn meal to milk mixture and cook as mush.
Beat together remaining ingredients while cooking mush.
When good and thick add egg mixture, beat well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot from the oven.
A favorite of all our family!

title: corn relish
directions: Cook corn on cob just enough to set milk (about 3 minutes). Cut from cob; put cabbage, onions and peppers through food chopper, using coarse blade.
Combine all vegetables.
Blend salt, flour, turmeric, sugar and mustard.
Add vinegar gradually.
Bring to a boil and add to the vegetables.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes. Seal at once in hot sterilized jars.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs lengthwise in half.
Slip out yolks and mash with fork.
Mix in seasonings and salad dressing.
Fill whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping it up slightly.

title: ceviche
directions: Combine fish and lemon juice in a glass bowl.
Marinate 2 hours.
Drain and discard marinade.

title: marshmallow puffs
directions: In large bowl, pour milk over first five ingredients.
Mix well and roll in balls and then in coconut.
Chill 1/2 hour or more on cookie sheet in refrigerator.

title: fish courtbouillion
directions: Cover fish and seasoning with water.
Use cast-iron pot.
Layer cooking oil, fish, onion, bell pepper, garlic and V-8.
Pour Ro-Tel tomatoes and dissolved Tony Chachere instant roux over layers. Cover pot and cook over low flame.
Every ten or so minutes, remove cover and gently shake pot.
Do not stir.
Stirring breaks up the fish.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oreo frozen dessert
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush Oreos.
Add melted butter and press into pan.
Freeze.
Slice ice cream; arrange on top of Oreos and let soften to cover crust.
Freeze.

title: chicken tikka
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend spices together with yoghurt, salt, lemon juice, coloring and tomato puree.
Add chicken pieces and coat well.
Leave overnight or for at least 3 hours.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: In a large kettle, cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender.
Drain, reserving liquid, and set aside.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Shape into large meatballs and brown in oil.
Pour in tomato sauce mixture and cook for about 45 minutes on low, until the rice is done.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat together egg, sugar, cream cheese, vanilla and lemon extracts.
Set aside.
Press graham cracker crumb mixture into 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Pour cream cheese mixture into graham cracker crust and bake at 325° for approximately 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and pour your favorite pie filling on top.

title: chocolate fruit bars
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream shortening; add sugar, egg and vanilla.
Stir in fruit.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together and place crushed saltines with butter on top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lime chiffon squares
directions: Combine margarine and crumbs.
Press firmly into bottom of a 9-inch square or 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
In a large mixing bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk, pineapple and lime juice.
Fold in marshmallows and whipped cream. Pour into prepared dish.
Chill 2 hours or until set.
Garnish as desired.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, egg and butter together thoroughly.
Stir in milk. Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Spread batter in a greased and floured 9-inch square pan.

title: pork chops with savory apple glaze
directions: Serves 4; 136 calories, 3 g fat and 20 mg cholesterol.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar in large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Stir in 1/2 cup of candies.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: oreo cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy.
Add milk. Beat until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add 1/2 cup of chips and the flour and mix well. Pour over crust.
Pour remainder of chips on top.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: chunk o' cheese meat loaf
directions: Blend meat with chopped mushrooms, onion, parsley, bread crumbs, egg, salt, pepper and milk until blended.
Dice cheese into 1/2-inch cubes.
Blend into meat mixture (by hand), making sure to distribute the cheese chunks evenly.
Pack into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Pour off liquid.

title: 20 minute sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil and garlic.
Add vegetables and stir-fry 1 minute or until crisp-tender.
Combine bouillon, soy sauce, sherry, vinegar, brown sugar, ginger and pineapple with juice.
Bring to boil.
Stir in Minute rice.
Cover.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken and vegetables and serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: basic cream pie
directions: Mix
sugar
and flour; add egg yolks and enough milk to blend well.
When
mixture
is smooth, add remainder of milk. Mix
well and cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.	Remove from
heat
and
add
butter,
vanilla and, if desired,
or
2 drops
of yellow food coloring.
Pour into cooked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: carolyn's brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with shortening.
Take off heat; add sugar, then eggs.
Beat.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla. Add nut and chocolate chips, if desired.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Kill 1 moose (elk may be substituted).
Dip moose in vat of chocolate.
Let drip dry.
Serves 3,000.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Add cheese.
Cook lasagna and drain. Fry onions in butter.
Grease an oblong pan with butter.
Add a little milk to prevent sticking.
Layer noodles and potatoes; top with onions.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pain francais(french bread)
directions: Measure warm water into large mixing bowl; sprinkle in yeast to dissolve.
Add salt, shortening and flour, stirring until well blended.
Dough will be slightly sticky.
Place in a greased bowl; turn to grease top.
Cover and let rise 12 hours, or until double in size.
Form long loaf.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.
Brush with egg white mixed with water.
Reduce temperature to 425°. Bake for 5 minutes longer on bottom shelf.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in little oil until it gets tender.
Add broth, vegetables and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer.
Combine 1/4 cup water and cornstarch.
Stir into the meat.
Serve over rice.

title: baked beans
directions: Add brown sugar, white sugar, bacon and Velveeta cheese to remaining ingredients.
Bake uncovered at 300° for about 2 hours.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions and bake.
While hot, poke holes in cake and pour sweetened condensed milk over cake.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream together the Philly cream cheese and tomato soup.
Add chopped onion, green pepper, shrimp, mayonnaise, gelatine, garlic powder and salt. Serve with crackers.

title: garden spiral primavera
directions: Cook spirals according to package directions.
In large skillet, heat oil and butter.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add the remaining vegetables.
Cook 3 more minutes, stirring frequently.
Add wine and seasonings. Simmer 5 minutes or until tender.
Toss spirals with vegetables. Add cheese.
Serve immediately.
Yield:

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients and bake in uncovered casserole dish for 25 minutes.

title: carrots elegante
directions: Cook carrots, covered, in 1/2-inch boiling water 8 minutes; drain.
Turn carrots into a 1-quart baking dish.
Stir in raisins, butter, honey, lemon juice and ginger.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 375° oven 35 minutes; stir occasionally.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Yields 4 servings.

title: old country apple pie
directions: Beat eggs and pour over sliced apples.
Mix together the sugar, nuts, raisins and cinnamon.
Add apples.
Add vanilla and vegetable oil to apples.
Mix. Sift together every ingredient and mix. Mixture will be thick.
Turn into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: deer or beef jerky
directions: Cut meat in strips 1/4 inch thick, 3 inches long and 1/2 inch wide.
Put meat in 2-inch deep pan.
Mix other ingredients with 1 glass of water, then add enough water to cover meat.
Soak meat for 24 to 36 hours.
Stir every 10 hours to coat well.
After soaking, place meat on paper towels to drain water.
Sprinkle one side with red pepper.
Move oven rack to top of oven.
Place toothpick through end of meat and hang on rack.
Put oven on lowest setting.
Use spoon to crack door open.
Cook 8 to 12 hours; if crunchy at 8 hours, take out.
After cooling, store in jar in refrigerator.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine ingredients except grated cheese in small casserole dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, until bubbly.
Serve hot with crackers.
Makes about 15 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and pat in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in tube (or Bundt) pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Cool in pan about 15 minutes.
Remove from pan, perforate cake and pour glaze over it while still warm.

title: italian style halibut on grill
directions: In bowl, combine Italian salad dressing, lemon juice, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Place halibut steaks in sauce.
Let stand 30 minutes, turning once.
Place fish on grill, basting occasionally, with dressing mixture.
Cook fish for 5 to 7 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with fork. Before serving, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: easy bake meat balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ground beef, onion, egg and cracker crumbs and shape into meatballs.
Pour cream of celery soup and half a can of water over top of meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, add baked potatoes and have a quick, delicious meal.
Serves 4.
