title: pork chop supreme
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Season with salt, if desired.
Place chops in large baking dish.
Top each chop with an onion slice and a lemon or orange slice.
Place 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon catsup on each chop.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Uncover and bake at 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.

title: crock-pot hot cocoa for a group
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add hot water slowly, mixing well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.

title: karen's lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In skillet, heat oil over moderate heat. Add beef, onion and garlic and cook 7 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally until meat is no longer pink.
Drain off any fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato liquid, tomato paste, 1 tablespoon of parsley, oregano, salt, basil and pepper to skillet.

Reduce heat to low and simmer about 1 hour, stirring occasionally, until thick. Meanwhile, in a medium size bowl, mix cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, eggs and remaining 2 tablespoons parsley with a fork until well mixed.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut corn from cobs and scrape cobs to remove all milk.
Heat butter and bacon drippings in a medium saucepan until hot.
Add corn, water, salt and pepper.
Cook uncovered over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Serves 10.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, onion and salt in 2 cups water about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Lightly mash with a potato masher and cook, stirring constantly, until soup is hot and thickened.

title: dutch apple bread
directions: Mix all, except apples, real well.
Will look like biscuit dough.
Place in baking dish.
Push apples into dough.

title: cheese quiche (grape-nut)
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Reserve 1 tablespoon drippings.
Saute onion in reserved bacon drippings until tender and lightly browned.
Combine eggs, milk, cheese, salt, pepper and cereal.
Stir in onion and bacon.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Mix and pour into ice cups and freeze.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies fine and pour in bowl.
Set aside.
Then mix milk and vanilla pudding together in a large bowl.
Add Cool Whip.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and butter (melt butter).
Fold beans into mixture (mix well).
Bake in 9-inch pie pan with unbaked pie crust (350°) for about 1 hour.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken in approximately 3 quarts (12 cups) of water. When done, remove meat from bones and place back in broth.
Add chopped celery, sliced carrots and chopped onion.
Allow to simmer 20 to 30 minutes on low heat or until vegetables are done.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Combine and mix well the sugar, flour, salt and vanilla.
Add rhubarb and strawberries; mix well and put into pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Add top crust and cut slits in crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce oven to 350° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: cranberry freeze
directions: Spoon into 13 x 9 baking dish.
Freeze 4 hours or overnight. Cut into squares.

title: gram's donuts
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Add hot to additional ingredients. Roll out dough.
Cut.
Drop into hot oil until golden brown. Place on paper towel.
Drop donuts in cinnamon/sugar or powdered sugar for variation.

title: stollen
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk; add flour and remaining ingredients (except glaze).
Knead dough well, then let rise in warm oven until double in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Glaze if desired.

title: swiss sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage until browned.
Mash with potato masher until fine.
Drain well.
Combine mustard with sausage and blend.
Cut bread slices diagonally.
Space half of bread in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Top with cheese slices.
Space remaining bread slices evenly over cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until egg sets.
Great for a guest brunch!

title: lemon pie
directions: In a medium bowl, combine milk and juice.
Let stand a few minutes.
Stir in whipped topping.
Add food coloring, if desired. Spoon into crust.
Chill until firm.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ham nibbles
directions: Combine ham, drained canned corn, mayonnaise, eggs and 1 cup cracker crumbs in medium bowl. Shape mixture in small balls about 1 1/2-inches in diameter. Roll in remaining cracker crumbs. Fry in deep hot fat (365° to 375°), 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown. Drain on absorbent paper. Yield: 2 1/2 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together sugar, oil and eggs; blend in flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and vanilla. Mix well. Add zucchini and nuts. Blend by hand. Pour into 13 x 5 x 3 loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: easy caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Place popped corn in large brown paper sack.
Combine brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt in a 1 1/2-quart batter bowl. Cook on High for 2 minutes or until bubbly.
Stir; cook for 2 minutes or until bubbly.
Stir; cook for 2 minutes more on High. Add soda and stir until mixture is foamy.
Pour mixture over popcorn.
Fold bag and place into microwave.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Take out and shake like crazy.
Place in microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake again and pour onto waxed paper.

title: turkey buns(quick!)
directions: Melt margarine in frypan over medium-high heat.
Add onions and green pepper; saute until limp.
Add turkey, mixing well. Cook until no longer pink, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except buns.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon onto buns.
Yields 8 servings.

title: pumpkin pie smoothie
directions: Remove pumpkin from can; freeze 1 hour.
In a blender, combine partially frozen pumpkin, frozen apple juice concentrate, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Blend together until smooth.
Continue to blend while adding water to fill the blender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: texas style potatoes
directions: Melt butter in dish. Cut potatoes up and place in dish. Sprinkle garlic salt, pepper and chili powder over potatoes. Place chopped onions and peppers over the top of the potatoes. Cover with foil. Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: molded ambrosia
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine; reserve 1/3 for topping.
Press remaining crumb mixture into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot water; stir in reserved syrup.
Chill until partially set.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Whip until fluffy.
Fold in pineapple, oranges and coconut.
Pour over crumbs in pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top.
Chill until firm.
Cut in squares.
Trim with maraschino cherries, if desired.
Serves 9.

title: music salad
directions: Mix the jello with the boiling water and cool.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Put in mold to set.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in container. Use approximately 1/2 cup mix to each cup of hot water.

title: turketti(low-fat)
directions: Break spaghetti in 2-inch lengths.
Cook.
Drain well.
Mix chopped turkey, pimento, green pepper, onion, soup, broth and pepper.
Add Velveeta cheese and spaghetti.
With two forks, lightly toss until well mixed.

title: frozen chocolate dessert
directions: Crush cookies in blender or food processor.
Reserve some cookie crumbs for garnish.
Put remaining crumbs in 9 x 13 pan and drizzle with melted margarine.
Let set in freezer.
Cover with softened ice cream.
Freeze.

title: chicken with walnuts
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces; set aside.
In small bowl, stir soy sauce into cornstarch; stir in dry sherry, ginger root, sugar, salt and red pepper.
Set aside.
Preheat a wok over high heat.
Add oil; stir-fry green peppers and onions in hot oil for 2 minutes, or until crisp-tender.
Remove from wok.
Add half of the chicken to hot oil (add more oil, if necessary); stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove from wok.
Stir-fry remaining chicken for 2 minutes.
Return all chicken to wok.
Stir in soy mixture.
Cook until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in vegetables and walnuts. Cover and cook 1 minute more.
Serve chicken and vegetables at once.
Serve with hot cooked rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: dirt
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.

title: chocolate pies
directions: First lightly brown pie shells in oven.
Set aside to cool. In a double boiler, melt margarine.
Add milk.
Separate egg yolks.
Save whites and store in refrigerator.
Stir egg yolks with spoon and add to milk and butter mixture in a double boiler (before milk gets hot).
In a bowl, mix together sugar, salt, flour and cocoa.
Add to mixture in double boiler.
Stir continually until filling thickens.
Add flavoring.
Pour filling in pie shells.
Beat egg whites until foamy; add 1/2 cup of sugar and beat until stiff.
Spread over pies and lightly brown in a 350° oven.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for cake together and bake for 40 minutes in an oven preheated to 350°.

title: ham balls with raisin sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In large bowl with hands, lightly mix ham ball ingredients and 1/4 teaspoon pepper until combined. Shape into 12 balls, divided evenly. Arrange in shallow baking dish. Bake uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook peppers, onion and eggplant in the bacon grease for 4 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt, cheese and bread crumbs.
Put in 2-quart baking dish, greased, and top with bread crumbs, bacon and cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine coconut and milk.
Set aside.
Blend margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add coconut mixture.
Mix well and turn into pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: date nut balls
directions: Combine
butter,
sugar
and
dates.
Cook 5 minutes on medium heat, stirring until well blended.
Add coconut, nuts, Rice Krispies, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Shape into balls and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: chicken el paso
directions: On waxed paper, combine crumbs and chili powder.
In shallow dish, dip chicken into dressing.
Coat with crumb mixture.
On baking sheet, arrange chicken.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, turning once during baking.
Serve with salsa.
Makes 4 servings.
Prep Time:
5 minutes.
Cook Time: 20 minutes.

title: baked chicken in  honey sauce(makes 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add honey, orange juice, lemon juice, mustard, salt and curry powder.
Mix well.
Coat chicken pieces with honey mixture and place, skin-side down, in baking dish.

title: traditional chex party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Heat butter in a large, shallow roasting pan in oven until melted.
Remove.
Stir in salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add Chex cereals and nuts.
Mix until all pieces are coated.
Heat in oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes until done.
Spread on paper towel to absorb excess oil until cool, then pour in bowl.

title: confetti refrigerator dessert
directions: Bake and cool cake as directed on package.
Tear cake into about 1-inch pieces.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in large bowl on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally until smooth and creamy.
Beat whipping cream in chilled bowl until stiff.
Gently fold whipped cream, cherries and marshmallows into cream cheese mixture.
Toss cake pieces and cream cheese mixture. Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Refrigerate until set, about 8 hours.
Refrigerate any remaining dessert.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: chewy rice krispies
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat; add marshmallows, stirring until completely melted.
Add the rest of the ingredients until well mixed.
Press mixture into evenly buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: delightful potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on with bay leaves; peel and cut. Mix
remaining
ingredients.
Spread
over	potatoes
in casserole.	Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel candy popcorn
directions: Over medium heat, melt oleo.
Stir in sugar, syrup and salt. Stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla. Put corn in large pan and pour syrup over it.
Stir until well mixed.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix well with mixer at medium speed.
Bake in 3 layers at 350°.

title: fudge
directions: Place sugar, margarine and milk in medium size heavy pan.
With heat set on medium, stir constantly with wooden spoon until temperature reaches 234° or to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add chips first; stir.
Then add cream, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
"Enjoy."

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and put in greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: foolproof apple cake
directions: Combine oil and eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to oil mixture.
Add apples and nuts. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Remove from heat and add jello. Dissolve and cool.
Pour over quart of strawberries in a baked pie shell.
Chill.

title: frosted pecans
directions: Beat the egg white until frothy.
Add 1 tablespoon of water and mix in pecans.
In another bowl, mix 1 cup of sugar, cinnamon mix and add to the other ingredients.
Stir.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake for 1 hour at 200°.
Put in a paper bag and break it up.

title: molasses crinkles(cookies)
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses thoroughly with an electric mixer.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cloves, cinnamon and ginger together.
Mix dry ingredients into egg mixture.
Chill. Roll into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Dip tops of dough balls in sugar. Place balls, sugared side up, 3-inches apart, on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not hard.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup onions. Pour into casserole dish, bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake for an additional 5 minutes uncovered or until onions are golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Mix cooked potatoes and ham and put in casserole dish.
Saute onions in margarine.
Add flour, salt and pepper and make roux for sauce.
Add milk, stir until thickened.
Add cheese until melted. Pour over potato mixture and mix.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: easy ice cream cake
directions: Line frozen ice cream bar sandwiches into the bottom of a 9x12-in pan (cut to fit).
Cover with cool whip.
Use half the container.
Pour fudge topping over cool whip.
Line another layer of ice cream bar sandwiches.
Cover with the rest of the cool whip. Top with caramel ice cream topping.
Sprinkle with peanuts. Refrigerate.

title: mrs. harry m. schoppert's broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together saving 1/2 of cheese to put on top.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Before putting in oven, spread rest of cheese on top.
You can add almonds on top too, if you want.
Can be prepared a day or 2 ahead.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain and cool.
Place layers of carrots, onion and pepper in 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine all other ingredients; mix well.
Pour over carrots.
Cover with plastic wrap or aluminum foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° until bubbly.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: chili oil
directions: The secret
to
a
good mustard dipping sauce is to add 1/3 part
white
vinegar
to
2/3 parts water when mixing with your powdered mustard for dipping your prawns, won tons, etc.

title: baked carrot ring
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In mixer, cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs and beat well.
Add carrots and mix.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add these ingredients to first mixture and mix only until well combined.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: soup
directions: Place pork loin in a 4 to 6-quart covered stockpot and cover with water.
Cook until meat is tender; cool slightly and slice or cube as desired.
Place the meat and vegetables in the remaining broth and add the V-8 juice.
Simmer until vegetables are tender. Serve with crackers and/or cornbread.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Arrange tomatoes and cheese in bottom of shallow dish.
In a small jar, with tight fitting lid, place corn oil, vinegar, parsley, onion, basil, salt and pepper. Cover and shake well. Pour over tomatoes and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate several hours, spooning herb mixture over tomatoes occasionally.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Roll out crackers to a fine meal.
Mix all dry ingredients to crackers.
Melt marshmallows in milk over a double boiler on low heat.
Stir to keep from burning.
Pour mixed fruit and meal.
Mix well.
Pack back into cracker box and store in icebox.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Drain juices from pineapple and grapes.
Add pineapple, cut up cherries, grapes and bananas to marshmallows.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar, mayonnaise and cherry juice together.
Fold this mixture into marshmallows, pineapple, grapes and bananas.
Whip the cream (if using sweet cream); fold into mixture.
If using Cool Whip, fold into other mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: vegetable manicotti
directions: Microwave shells to desired doneness.
In small bowl combine zucchini, broccoli, mushrooms, Parmesan cheese and green pepper. Mix well and fill each shell with 1/2 cup of mixture.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over shells.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes, turning dish 1/4 turn halfway through cooking.
Sprinkle with cheese and microwave uncovered on High 1 to 2 minutes until cheese is melted. Makes 2 servings.

title: freezer daiquiri
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in glass or plastic container in deep freezer for 8 to 12 hours before serving.
About 30 minutes before serving, remove from freezer.
Mixture should be icy.
Any portion not used may be frozen again.
You may want to omit one can of pink lemonade and add one 10 ounce package of frozen strawberries.
For a tart taste, add juice of 2 lemons.
This will never freeze solid.
This recipe makes about 2 quarts or 20 to 25 cocktails.

title: tropical coconut pineapple bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 9 x 13 pan.
Prepare cake mix using 1/2 cup yogurt and 1 egg.
Spread batter onto the bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
While baking, in a bowl mix remaining yogurt, egg, pineapple, brown sugar and coconut. Carefully spread yogurt mixture on top of partially baked batter. Bake bars 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely before cutting into bars.
Mix confectioners sugar and 2 tablespoons reserved pineapple juice to create a glaze.
Drizzle over cooked bars.

title: mexican pile-upgroves, texas
directions: Brown meat slowly until browned then add taco sauce and water to cover.
Simmer until water is cooked out.

title: hazelnut chocolate candy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange 1 cup hazelnuts on jelly roll pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Wrap in kitchen towel and rub nuts to remove skins.
Cool, then coarsely chop.
Microwave 12 squares chocolate, chopped in bowl, on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes, stirring once halfway through, until smooth.
Stir in nuts.

title: norwegian coffee bread(norske kaffe brod)
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm.
Remove from heat and dissolve yeast in milk.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Stir in flour until smooth.
When smooth, sprinkle flour on top; cover and set on stove.
Let rise 1 hour or until double in size.

title: sushi su
directions: Combine the ingredients; boil gently until dissolved.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together.
Add enough of the water to make a paste.
Beat in egg yolks well. Heat remaining water with butter and salt until butter is melted.
Add water mixture to first mixture and cook until thick.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla.
Cool and pour into baked 9-inch pie shell. Cover with meringue and brown.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Cook raisins in small amount of water for 12 minutes.
Drain water off raisins.
Add the rest of ingredients; cook until thick, then cool.
Pour into the pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: peanut butter snowballs
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, peanut butter and oleo; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on a waxed lined cookie sheet.
Chill for 30 minutes, or until firm.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 3 gallons.

title: italian chicken
directions: Dredge each chicken breast halve in flour; dip in egg and coat with bread crumbs.
Heat vegetable oil in a skillet over medium high heat.
Cook chicken 2 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Place chicken in a 9-inch square baking dish; set aside. Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over chicken. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in bottom of dish.
Make sure it covers the whole bottom of the dish.
Sprinkle a layer of graham cracker crumbs, covering the bottom.
Pat down with a spoon.
Next, add a layer of chocolate chips, then add a layer of coconut.
Cover with Pet milk (evenly).
Bake at 350° until golden.
Let cool for 30 minutes.

title: italian cheese-herb bread
directions: Brush French bread halves with Italian dressing; top with American cheese slices or grated Cheddar cheese, tomato slices, sliced onion and chopped fresh basil.
Broil until cheese begins to melt.

title: golden lemon chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then flour.
In 12-inch skillet, melt butter and brown chicken over medium heat 4 minutes, turning once. Stir in soup mix, blended with water.
Arrange lemon slices on chicken.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, covered, 10 minutes, or until sauce is slightly thickened and chicken is done.

title: banana cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red beans with tomato sauce
directions: Soak beans 2 or 3 hours; drain.
Chop cooked bacon finely. Place in large saucepan with water; cover.
Boil 10 minutes.
Then add beans, tomato sauce, onion, pepper pods, garlic, bay leaf, cumin seeds, salt and pepper.
Cover and let simmer 3 hours or until beans are tender.
Stir often.
Add more water or tomato sauce as needed.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: granola bars
directions: Blend 2nd bowl with 1st bowl and mix well.
Spoon into paper lined muffin tins and bake at 325 for about 45 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: roast beef and gravy
directions: Rub roast with salt and pepper.
Mix soups and water.
Put half of mixture into aluminum foil.
Add meat and cover with other half of mixture.
Close and cook at 325° until tender.
Take up roast with delicious gravy.

title: quick veggies and pasta
directions: Boil noodles and vegetables approximately 10 minutes.
Drain. Add butter and salt to taste.
Serve with Parmesan cheese and parsley.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Cook remaining ingredients in a baking dish, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: clam fritters
directions: Heat oil to 375°.
Mix all ingredients until thick and stays on spoon.
Pat batter into pan to form patty.
Brown on each side. Serve hot.
Good leftover and in sandwiches.

title: pfeffernuesse
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate 1 day.
Take 1 tsp. of batter and roll into ball (approximately size of walnut).
Use powdered sugar on hands, if it sticks.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Bake until no indentation remains when touched.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Will keep for months at room temperature in a glass container.
They stay nice and soft.

title: three potato salad
directions: Place all potatoes in Dutch oven. Cover with water. Bring to boil. Reduce heat. Cook 20 or 30 minutes. Drain and cool. Place potatoes in a large bowl. Add onion. In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Pour over potato mixture and toss gently to coat. Cover and refrigerate. Makes 15 servings.

title: sunday sunday chicken
directions: In medium bowl, combine soups, butter and rice.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken pieces over rice mixture.
Brush with remainder of butter.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 275° for about 2 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender. Very good.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt remaining margarine and add to beaten eggs, milk, bread, sugar and other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: hard-boiled egg casserole
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a saucepan over low heat.
Add onion and cook until tender. Combine flour and milk with butter and onion, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add cheese until melted.
Layer half of the eggs in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch dish. Pour half the onion and cheese mixture over the eggs.
Sprinkle half of the potato chips and half of the bacon over the mixture. Repeat this process with the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream together all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shells (not the deep-dish). Bake in a 400° oven for 25 minutes. Makes 3 or 4 pies.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine cider and cinnamon sticks in pot and bring to a boil. Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve hot in mugs; garnish with apple wedges.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, add sauce; simmer a few minutes.
In a small saucepan, mix soup and green chilies; warm for a few minutes.
Pour beef mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 2 layers of tortillas.
Pour in soup mixture, top with cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: good candy!
directions: Combine chocolate and butterscotch chips in a double boiler until melted.
Add nuts and noodles to chocolate mixture.
Cover cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Put by teaspoonful on cookie sheet and put in freezer.
Store in freezer, taking out shortly before serving.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Melt cheese in soup.
Add drained tomatoes and drained hominy. Cover with crushed Fritos and bake at 350° until warm, about 20 minutes.

title: microwave custard
directions: Microwave milk in a 2-quart dish on High for 3 to 4 minutes until almost boiling.
Mix together eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla and add to milk, stirring to mix.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Cook on Medium-high, rotating dish occasionally until knife comes out clean.

title: vegetable beef and chicken casserole
directions: In skillet, brown beef; spoon off fat.
Stir in soups, water, mixed vegetables and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until hot. Meanwhile, cut each biscuit into quarters.
Remove dish from oven; stir.
Arrange biscuits on hot mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Blend butter and flour in saucepan until smooth.
Add half and half and milk, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add bouillon cubes and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Add cooked broccoli.

title: cherry or strawberry winks
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients together, adding just enough liquid to make a stiff dough.
Drop from teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Optional:
Either place chopped cherries or cherry halves on small indentation in middle of cookie or mix all cherries (chopped) in dough.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove and cool on rack.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Grate zucchini.
Add eggs, salt, pepper, parsley and grated cheese.
Add enough flour to hold shape when dropped by tablespoonfuls into hot, shallow oil.
Brown on both sides and drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and cocoa in a medium saucepan. Add yolks of eggs and milk. Mix well. Add margarine. Mix and cook on medium heat, stirring constantly with a rubber spatula. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Stir. Pour filling into crust and top with meringue.

title: cheesy chicken over rice
directions: Put all in skillet; stir until well blended and bubbling hot. Serve over rice.

title: queema (ground beef) or beef
directions: Cut and fry onion in vegetable oil until red.
Add meat and other ingredients.
Let it cook on high heat for about 5 minutes, then turn the heat down.
Let it cook until the meat is tender.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix as for a cake.
Put in a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle 2 cups cherries over this and 1 cup sugar over the cherries.
Cover all with 2 cups of boiling water.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
(Raspberries or other fruits may be substituted and adjust the sugar accordingly.)

title: mona's tamale pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Drain corn and pureed tomatoes.
Add to the meat.
Add taco mix.
Pour mixture into greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese and cornbread mix.
Bake for 30 minutes or until cornbread is golden.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook and drain egg noodles.
Saute onion and pepper in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Combine and mix well, mushroom soup, salad dressing, mustard, milk, tuna fish and cooked egg noodles.
Add onion and pepper to above mixture.
Bake on 425° for 1/2 hour. Serve hot.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Melt butter in milk; heat to scalding point.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix all ingredients, except lemon pudding mix; pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven until lightly browned.
Cut the cake into 2 layers. Prepare 1 package of lemon pudding mix; spoon onto bottom layer. Place top layer on top of the pudding.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 4 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You can pour into 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans and bake for 45 minutes.

title: avocado taco dip
directions: Spread refried beans on large platter.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco mix; spread on beans.
Spread with avocado mix. Spread with chopped olives.
Spread with grated Cheddar cheese. Use any kind of chips or crackers to dip with.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: bishop sheen's meat loaf
directions: Put meat in bowl.
Add onions, peppers, bread, garlic, parsley, egg, salt, pepper and applesauce; mix well.
Form into loaf shape; flour well.
Oil pan and place floured loaf in pan. Add catsup on top of loaf.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350°° for 2 hours.
Uncover for last 15 minutes.

title: diet waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Heat waffle iron and use a cup measure to pour batter onto waffle iron. Cook until golden brown. Serve hot with fresh fruit slices.

title: breakfast apples
directions: Combine all ingredients except apples; bring to a boil.
Pare apples, core, cut in eights and add to syrup.
Cook slowly until done, 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool in syrup.
Remove spices and lemon.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Mix all together (chips last) and bake.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil first 3 ingredients.
Mix together the last 6 ingredients.
Pour liquid mixture into dry mixture and beat until well mixed.
Bake in a 15 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broiled scallops
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute garlic.
Place scallops in oiled baking dish; pour butter over them.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and cheese over scallops and broil 6 to 8 minutes.
Serve with lemon slices.

title: chokecherry wine
directions: Keep in warm place 21 days.
Stir and let stand another 21 days; strain.
Ready to bottle up.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar and pretzels together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix strawberry Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water and the strawberries.
Cool until the mixture begins to set.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and whipped topping; spread on top of cooled crust.
Cover with strawberry mixture and refrigerate.

title: bean casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
Drain immediately and run cold water over eggs. Peel eggs and place in narrow, deep jar.
In medium saucepan, combine all other ingredients except sliced onions.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Place onion slices on top of eggs; pour hot vinegar on top of eggs, making sure they are completely covered.
Cover tightly; refrigerate for several days.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients
except
nuts together.
Stir well and beat for
5 minutes with mixer.
Spray Bundt pan very good with Pam.
Add
nuts to mix and stir well.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 325°
for one hour, but remove the instant it is done. Let cool to lukewarm.
Leave in pan.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy mexican brunch eggs(serves 8 to 12)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Over medium heat, cook sausage, mushrooms and onion.
Drain well.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Combine eggs and sour cream in blender.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish (greased).
Bake until eggs are softly set, 5 to 10 minutes.
Spoon salsa over eggs.
Add sausage mixture.
Top with Velveeta, then Mozzarella and Cheddar.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Pour 1/3 batter into greased tube pan.
Sprinkle with 1/3 chocolate chips.
Mix 1/3 more batter with all of chocolate syrup.
Pour on top of other batter.
Sprinkle with 1/3 more chocolate chips.
Pour rest of batter on top and sprinkle with rest of chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: my own beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato.
Add potato when stew is almost done.
Bring stew to boil and then lower to simmer until done.

title: eloise's crab cakes
directions: Mix well. Make patty cakes or put in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 6.

title: creamed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes with salt and margarine until tender. Drain well. Whip.
Beat in cream cheese and sour cream.
Pour into buttered baking dish. Sprinkle grated cheese on top, if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Best if made up the night before. Store tightly covered in refrigerator overnight before baking.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Sort and wash peas; place in a heavy saucepan.
Cover with water and bring to a boil; cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Cover and let soak 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Form in large ball.
Roll in nuts.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.

title: cheesy macaroni bake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray a 6-cup, shallow baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Cut cheeses into cubes.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
If using fresh broccoli, put in with macaroni 3 minutes before pasta is done.
Drain macaroni; leave in pot.
Add Cheddar, Mozzarella, bacon
bits, mustard, salt and red pepper.
If using thawed, frozen broccoli, add it now. Spoon mixture into the prepared baking dish.
Pour milk evenly over top.
Bake until bubbly and golden, 18 to 21 minutes.
Makes 4 servings (1 1/4 cups).

title: baby potatoes with garlic and rosemary
directions: Steam potatoes until tender, about 20 minutes.
Saute garlic in olive oil for a minute or two, then add rosemary and saute another minute.
Toss drained potatoes in garlic mixture.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: strawberries
directions: Stir coconut, pecans and 1 package jello.
Add milk and extract.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight, covered.

title: our mary's crock-pot beans
directions: Fry bacon and break up into pieces.
Fry hamburger.
Fry onion.
Put all ingredients into crock-pot and can cook all day.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip the cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly.
Fold topping in.
Pour into crust; chill until firm.
Top with chocolate syrup.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 12-inch baking dish with Pam.
Mix ingredients and put in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour or until brown.

title: oyster stew
directions: Saute shallots in 4 Tbsp. of butter for 5 minutes.
Add oysters with their liquor.
Bring to a boil, add milk and cream, salt, and pepper.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Add sherry and again bring to a boil.
Serve at once, with a tsp. of butter in each serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Pour into double boiler and cook until mixture coats spoon and is thick.
Into a medium sized dish or bowl, layer wafers and thin slices of banana.
Add vanilla to pudding mixture after removing from stove.
Mix well. Pour pudding into the bowl.
Let cool.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix ingredients
together with enough Bisquick to thicken. Drop by teaspoons into hot oil and fry until brown.

title: candy
directions: Melt almond bark and Crisco oil together.
Add remaining ingredients. Place on foil on 2 cookie sheets.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken curry
directions: Boil chicken until done; save broth.
Fry onion in oil until clear.
Add chicken pieces, green mango, curry and flour until browned.
Add broth and tomatoes.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Serve over rice, if desired.

title: easy chewy pecan squares
directions: Blend ingredients until just moistened.
Spread mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven. Cool; cut into squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yields 24 (2-inch) squares.

title: ham with red-eye gravy
directions: In large skillet, over medium heat, brown a thick slice of ham about 1/2-inch thick; turn and cook until browned and heated through.
Remove ham to platter.
Add 2 cups water to pan drippings over medium heat, with spoon stir drippings to loosen from bottom of pan, heat to boiling and boil 5 minutes stirring occasionally.
Serve gravy over ham with grits.
Delicious with biscuits.

title: hot ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Slice ham and cheese into long strips to fit each row of rolls.
Halve rows, a row at a time, and place ham and cheese strips inside rolls.
Pour mixture over rolls and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350° until cheese is thoroughly melted.

title: white chili(lighter eating - 1.5 points per cup)
directions: Combine all ingredients in crockpot. Cook on low 8-10 hours or high for 4-5 hours.

title: apple pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; add pecans, apples, eggs, and margarine. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popcorn; mix well.
Spread into large shallow baking pans or cookie sheets.
Bake in oven at 250° for 1 hour.

title: mini meat loaves 'n vegetables
directions: Combine meat, salt, egg, 1/2 can tomato sauce, Italian seasoning and 1/2 can French fried onions.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, form 3 mini loaves.
Place potatoes around loaves.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 35 minutes.
Place vegetables around loaves; stir to combine with the potatoes.
Lightly season with salt and pepper, if desired.
Top meat loaves with remaining tomato sauce. Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Top loaves with remaining onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Makes 3 to 6 servings.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket with pepper and paprika.
Slice onions on top to cover.
Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over meat. Marinate overnight.
Bake at 300° to 325° for about 3 to 4 hours, depending on oven and thickness of meat.
When ready to serve, slice very thinly against the grain and serve with sauce.

title: curry dip
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in blender and process for 30 seconds.
Add last 3 ingredients and process about 15 seconds. Contents per tablespoon: calories 9, sodium 44 mg.

title: rose's cheese balls
directions: Let cream cheese get to room temperature.
(Important to have cream cheese soft.)
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in fridge until hard.
Shape.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except Coke and marshmallows in a large mixing bowl.
Blend at low speed; beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Add Coke; blend well.
By hand, stir in marshmallows. Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Cool about 30 minutes.
Spread with Cola Icing.

title: black cherry yummmm
directions: Drain liquid from cherries and pineapple into saucepan or measuring cup.
Add enough Coke to make 1 cup.
Heat to boil and add Jell-O.
Let cool to room temperature.
Add rest of Coke and other ingredients.
Pour into an 8-inch square dish.
Refrigerate until jelled.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Mix salad dressing and sugar together.
Sift flour, soda and cocoa together and combine with other mixture.
Add water and vanilla.
Bake in two layers at 350° until done.
Frost with 7 Minute Frosting.

title: chicken with dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in boiling, salted water until tender.
Remove chicken, saving 4 cups broth.
Debone chicken; set aside.
Skim broth, saving 6 tablespoons chicken fat.
Combine 6 tablespoons flour with fat in bowl; blend well.
Add a small amount of reserved broth, stirring until smooth.
Stir flour into 4 cups of broth in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: soon to be your favorite party dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and blend until smooth. The consistency of the dip can be controlled by the amount of lemon juice used. Chill thoroughly and serve with potato chips.

title: old fashioned chicken pot pie
directions: In sauce pan, melt butter.
Stir in flour, garlic, salt and pepper until well blended.
Gradually stir in water, milk and bouillon.
Bring to a boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in chicken and veggies, set aside.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain juice from whole corn.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a casserole dish and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: salmon cheese casserole
directions: Melt butter or margarine in scalded milk.
Pour over bread crumbs and allow to stand for 5 minutes.
Add cheese, salmon and salmon liquid to bread crumbs and mix well.
Add eggs, mix lightly and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp mornay
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in margarine.
Add shrimp and wine; cook 2 to 3 minutes or until shrimp are pink.
Remove vegetables and shrimp from pan with slotted spoon.
Add cream cheese and milk to pan.
Stir over low heat with wire whisk until smooth. Add Swiss cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Return shrimp and vegetables to pan; mix lightly.
Serve with rice or pasta.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pinto bean soup
directions: Cook onions slightly in butter.
Put into a blender with the beans, chicken stock, and seasonings and blend.
Transfer to a saucepan and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add tomato juice.
Heat and serve.
Float 1 tablespoon of fresh cream on top of each cup.

title: jello cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dough will be soft.
Place dough in a cookie press and place 1-inch apart on a cookie sheet. Put sprinkles on cookies and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Enjoy this great treat.

title: kielbasa delight
directions: Cut kielbasa into 3-inch loaf pieces.
Spread over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pineapple, chili sauce and brown sugar and pour over kielbasa.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Baste frequently.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix all together with a wire whip.

title: candy popcorn
directions: Bring sugar, water and cream of tartar to boil, covered.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add margarine and baking soda. Pour over popcorn and stir thoroughly.
Must be cane sugar or it will just crumble up and not stick to the popcorn.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Form beef, rice, parsley, onion salt and garlic salt into walnut sized meatballs.
Parboil 1 medium whole head of cabbage.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add and mix next 4 ingredients.
Slowly add the oil while beating with electric mixer.

title: souper corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine soup, eggs and milk; stir in muffin mix until blended.
Gently fold in sausage.
Into greased 9-inch square baking pan, pour in muffin mixture.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chocolate pistachio bundt cake
directions: Beat cake mix, pudding mix, oil, water and orange juice.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat on high for 2 minutes.
Remove about 1/4 to 1/3 of batter to smaller bowl and set aside.
Add 3/4 cup Hershey's syrup to large batter and beat until mixed.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Take reserved batter and pour onto chocolate batter, keeping away from sides and tube.
Can substitute other pudding flavors, such as banana or chocolate. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet with Crisco.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat with mixer until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded teaspoonful 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
In another large bowl put shortening and sugar.
Cream together until fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in mashed bananas.
Add flour mixture, about 1/4 at a time.
Mix until smooth each time.
Mix in nuts and pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until bread is browned and pulls slightly away from sides of pan.
Let stand in pan 5 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup margarine, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese; stir well.
Spoon into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Crush cereal and stir into remaining butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Slice peaches and mix with 3/4 cup of sugar; let stand 2 hours.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix with 1 cup of sugar.
Stir in milk and almond extract.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Pour batter over butter; do not stir.
Pour the peaches over the top of the batter to form a layer.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes; with glass baking dish, bake at 325°.
Check as end of baking time approaches as you do not want the juices to caramelize.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: smoked kielbasi appetizer
directions: Slice smoked kielbasi in 1-inch slices.
Place in microwave dish.
Top kielbasi with 1 teaspoon of brown sugar.
With toothpicks, place a pineapple chunk on top.
Microwave for 2 to 3 minutes until hot.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add tomatoes and chili.
Mix well.
Simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: bread dressing and pork chops
directions: Break bread into bowl; pour milk, onion, egg, sage, salt and pepper over bread and mix.
Add more milk if needed to moisten bread.
Brown pork chops.
Place 2 chops in bottom of greased casserole; add dressing and put 2 chops on top.
Add a small amount of water to grease from chops; pour over top of casserole.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 4 servings.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray muffin tins with vegetable cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
In separate bowl, combine bananas, applesauce, egg and orange juice. Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into muffin tin and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: old time buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add flour and eggs, beat well. Stir buttermilk, vanilla flavoring, and nutmeg. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 45 to 50 min at 350°. Cool before serving. Serves 8.

title: baked squash
directions: Boil onion and chopped squash until tender and drain.
Add butter, mayonnaise, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Fold in cheese and pour into 8 x 8 greased casserole dish.	Top with Ritz crackers, crumbled and mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl. Serve immediately. Yield:
40 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Dissolve in hot water.
Add cold water, juice and ginger ale.
Makes approximately 30 cups.
The colder the better!

title: stuffed turkey loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium skillet, saute onion and celery in butter or margarine until translucent.
In a medium bowl, combine onion, celery, stuffing mix, eggs and water; mix well.
In a large bowl, combine ground turkey, plus half the stuffing mixture, mixed well.
Pat out half the turkey stuffing mixture in 4 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Spoon remaining stuffing over turkey mixture.
Pour tomato juice on top.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours, until turkey is no longer pink.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: remarkable fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to soft ball stage (cook on medium heat).
Stir often.
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, vanilla and nuts.
Mix until chocolate is melted and blended.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; cool and cut in squares.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mix well. Stir in flour, drop by tablespoonfuls into 1/2 inch hot oil. Cook until browned, turning once. Drain. Yield: 6 servings.

title: sorbet a la fraise(strawberry ice)
directions: Set aside 4 perfect strawberries with stems.
Wash and cap remaining strawberries.
Puree strawberries in blender, food processor (with a steel blade) or food mill.
Combine puree with confectioners sugar and lemon juice.
Pour mixture into a 1-quart metal pan or ice cube tray.
Freeze until mushy and frozen 1/2 inch around sides.

title: e-z cream cheese dips(serves 5)
directions: Mix 1 container cream cheese with marshmallow cream.
Serve with fruit.

title: bob's favorite chocolate chip-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter; add both sugars and molasses and cream well. Add eggs (beat 1 minute).
Add raisins, chips and nuts to mixture. Blend remaining ingredients into mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Take out when tops of cookies look doughy.
Makes a large batch.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Cream butter and just 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat in egg yolks. Blend in flour.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: meatball mix
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Mix well. Store in refrigerator up 2 months.

title: broccoli spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli and spinach according to directions on package. Mix all ingredients together, except cheese and cracker crumbs. Add cheese and crumbs on top and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening. Add sugar. Cream well. Add eggs. Mix thoroughly. Add dry ingredients. Then add mashed bananas and sour milk. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes a large loaf.

title: cold tomato - yogurt soup
directions: Puree tomatoes in processor or blender.
Add remaining ingredients except garnish and mix until smooth.
Taste and adjust seasoning.
Pour into bowl, cover and chill well.
Garnish each serving with yogurt and minced parsley.

title: ricki's make-ahead potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a Dutch oven or large kettle; cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook for 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Drain and place in a bowl; mash.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, 4 Tbsp. butter, onion and salt; stir until smooth and the cream cheese and butter are melted.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
Melt remaining butter; drizzle over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; uncover and bake 20 minutes longer. If potatoes are made ahead and refrigerated, let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes before baking.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: phyl's topari tree
directions: Insert endive on toothpicks all around a tree-shaped piece of Styrofoam.
Then insert remaining ingredients with toothpicks all around tree.
Curl carrots.

title: salamio roll
directions: Mix together all ingredients and knead for 5 minutes.
Pack tightly and cover.
Put in refrigerator.
Knead mixture for 5 minutes on the 2nd and 3rd day.
On the 4th day knead again for 5 minutes.
Form into 1 pound rolls.
Bake on broiler pan.
Set oven on 175° to 200°.
Bake for 4 hours.
Turn rolls every hour.
Meat will appear red when fully cooked.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in chips and nuts, if desired. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: baked hominy
directions: Beat egg well.
Add hominy and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Spoon into an 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350° or until top begins to brown.
Let set for a few minutes before serving.
Garnish with parsley, if desired. Serves 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheeses and mix all together.
Add 5 drops of Worcestershire sauce and sprinkle some garlic salt on it to taste. Form the cheeses into a ball with your hands.
Roll the cheese ball over the chopped pecans.
Serve with vegetable crackers.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat first 2 ingredients together in saucepan on stove.
Do not add water to Jell-O.
Mix next 2 ingredients in bowl and beat until mixture thickens.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip and mix well.
Dip vanilla wafers in milk and layer in a large dish.
Use half of the wafers for the first layer.
For second layer, layer half of the pudding mix.
Layer half of strawberry mixture for third layer. Repeat layers.
Top with wafers.

title: cheesy french bread
directions: Mix mayonnaise and butter.
Add cheese, onions, garlic and olives.
Split French bread lengthwise.
Spread half of mixture on each half of bread.
Place each half with butter side up on baking sheet in oven.
Bake at 350° until topping is crusty or until cheese melts.

title: fasnachts
directions: Bring milk and lard to the boiling point but do not boil. Stir in sugar and salt; let cool to lukewarm.
Beat eggs and add to the milk.
Soak yeast cake in 2 tablespoons warm water and keep warm.
Sift and measure the flour.

title: taco soup
directions: Can add onion, green chilies, Mexican tomatoes and chili beans.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Melt butter in a skillet over medium heat.
Stir in brown sugar, lemon juice, garlic and hot sauce.
Remove from heat.
In large skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Fry wings, turning occasionally for 10 minutes or until brown and very well done. Remove and drain on paper towels.
Keep hot, or bake wings in a single layer at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: creamy spinach and fettucini
directions: In skillet, melt 1/2 the butter, add garlic and onion, cook until golden.
Add spinach, cover pan, cook until spinach is heated through.
Meanwhile, cook noodles.
Drain and return to pot.
Toss with remaining butter, spinach mixture, Parmesan and cream until all are blended and heated through.
Serve immediately.

title: aunt hattie's corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into medium-size greased casserole dish.
Bake uncovered, 30 minutes, at 350°.

title: carrot bread
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil together.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake for 80 minutes at 325° in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pan.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Mix together chicken broth, refried beans, and tomatoes. Bring to a boil.
Shred chicken breasts, and add to the soup.
Cut flour tortillas in strips and bake at 350° until slightly browned. Place soup in individual bowls, top with cheese, then place tortilla chips on top.

title: instant cocoa
directions: Mix and store.
One serving is 3 teaspoons of mixture to 1 cup of boiling water.

title: broccoli salad 2
directions: Break florets into small pieces; add onion and cheese.
Dice bacon and fry until crisp; drain well and add to broccoli mixture. Combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Fill baked pie crust with sliced strawberries.
Bring sugar, cornstarch, Jell-O and water to boil.
Cook until mixture becomes clear looking.
Cool slightly.
Pour over sliced strawberries; refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: the "original" key lime pie
directions: Combine milk and lime juice.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks. Pour into pie shell and bake 10 minutes.
Make meringue by beating egg whites and cream of tartar and gradually adding sugar.
Cover pie with meringue, spreading to edges over crust.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned, about 10 minutes.

title: squash patties
directions: Boil the squash and onion in water until tender; drain.
Next add the cornmeal and egg.
Continue stirring and add the milk and cheese, if you prefer.
Drop the patties into hot grease, preferably in an iron skillet.
Cook just the same as you would any other type of patty.
Cook on low or medium.
Brown and drain on a paper towel.

title: chicken fried tacos
directions: Boil chicken breasts and debone; cut into small pieces.
Saute chopped onions in Wesson oil.
Add chicken and heat until piping hot.
Season with salt and pepper.
Thaw tortillas.
Fill with chicken and onions and roll up.
Stick with a toothpick to hold together.
Fry in hot grease.
Serve with Roy's Best of the Bayou picante sauce.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients; pour in casserole.
On top, put strips of Swiss cheese and almonds.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes.

title: coffee cake dough
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure water into large warm bowl; sprinkle in yeast. Stir until dissolved.
Stir in milk mixture, egg and 1/2 the flour; beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Cover loosely with aluminum foil; refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
(Dough may be kept in refrigerator up to 3 days.) Finish as directed in individual recipes.

title: sponge cake
directions: Sift together flour, 1 cup sugar and baking powder into small mixer bowl.
Measure egg whites, salt and cream of tartar into large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer at high speed until very soft mounds begin to form.
Beat 1/2 cup additional sugar into egg whites, a tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until very stiff, straight peaks form when beater is raised.
Do not underbeat.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Toss vegetables. Mix together mayonnaise, lemon juice, sugar and salt. Combine with vegetables. Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: strawberry cheese delight
directions: Make a coconut crust with coconut, sugar and flour.
Blend in margarine and press onto bottom of 9-inch spring pan or 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; chill.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix well.
Put small amount cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 60 minutes until bubbly.

title: artichoke spinach pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain and rinse with cold water. Combine cooled pasta, spinach, tomatoes, artichokes and cheese in a large bowl; toss gently.

title: pea soup
directions: Wash peas well.
Soak peas overnight in water to cover and then drain.
Put peas in soup kettle with 2 1/2 quarts of water, the cut up ham hocks and the sliced onion.
Add freshly ground black pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat so soup just simmers and cook for 2 hours.
I serve this with dark rye bread and butter.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: In casserole dish place a layer of potatoes (cut into pieces). Then add chopped onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Then add melted butter.
Chop the ham and add to this.
Pour mushroom soup on top of ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix margarine, powdered sugar and 1 cup flour together and pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
While baking, mix rest of ingredients together on low speed.
Pour on hot crust and continue baking for 20 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar while warm.
Cut when cool.

title: cookie cookies
directions: Mix
all dry ingredients until dry buds form.
Add egg. Roll into balls, place on cookie sheet, flatten.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.

title: sorghum cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add sifted ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes in 400° oven.

title: 48-hour cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and carrots. Mix together and stir in vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise. Salt and pepper to taste. Cover and refrigerate up to 48 hours before serving. Stir every 12 hours if possible. Great with fish or chicken. Serves 6.

title: chili
directions: Cook chopped onion slightly.
Add beef and brown until fairly done.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add garlic salt.
Blend in package of chili seasoning.
Add tomato paste plus three cans water.
Stir until blended.
Fold in beans and cook over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook as long as desired.
I usually let it simmer at least an hour and a half.

title: lime molded salad(nice on buffet table)
directions: Mix jello, boiling water and pineapple.
Chill until firm. Fold in sour cream.
Pour into mold.
Chill 3 hours or more. Serves 8 to 12.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together all ingredients except bacon.
Top with bacon slices.
Bake for 3 hours uncovered at 300°.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package and drain well.
Toss noodles, cream cheese, and butter together in pan.
Beat together in blender, eggs, sugar, milk and apricot nectar.
Turn noodle mixture into a buttered baking dish and pour egg mixture over the top.
Sprinkle with topping mix.
Bake 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Can be done ahead and refrigerated all day.

title: carrot-pineapple bundt cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour Bundt pan.
Mix together cake flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Drain pineapple, saving syrup.
Add pineapple syrup to dry
mixture; add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Stir in pineapple, carrots and nuts.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 minutes in pan before unmolding.
Frost with cream cheese glaze.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas, beating until light.
Alternately add flour and milk.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.

title: marinade for venison
directions: Marinate meat overnight.
If desired, partially cook peppers of your choice and onions, then bake or fry over meat.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except marshmallows, in electric mixer. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add marshmallows on top and bake for another 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Take chicken off the bone.
Mix soup and juice in a bowl and in a separate bowl mix melted margarine and stuffing mix.
In casserole dish, layer stuffing mix (reserve some to put on top), then chicken.
Pour soup and juice mixture over chicken, then top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Place frozen hash browns in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix melted butter, salt, onion soup, sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Spread mixture over hash browns.
Top with a mixture of melted butter and crushed cornflakes or bread crumbs if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: party dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Blend at high speed until creamy.
Serve with chips, crackers and fresh vegetables.

title: teriyaki sirloin steak
directions: Mix all ingredients except steak. Soak meat in mixture for 2 hours or longer, turning periodically. Remove from liquid and broil indoors or on barbecue.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Use mixer on medium speed to mix Crisco and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Continue to mix until well blended.
Add drained pineapple to mixture; then add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes at 400° on lightly greased cookie sheets.
While cookies are warm, glaze with confectioners sugar and pineapple juice, mixed together to make thin glaze.
Makes approximately four dozen.

title: lemon condensed pie
directions: Mix lemonade (thawed) with condensed milk and vanilla flavoring.
Fold in Cool Whip; stir until mixed well.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Makes 1 pie.
Double for 2 pies.
Keep chilled.

title: cream vegetables with meat and pasta
directions: Boil chicken; break in strips.
Set aside.
Saute onion and bell pepper until tender.
Cook rotini until tender.
Drain well. Steam mixed vegetables and drain.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Salt and pepper chicken, using garlic salt if desired.
Dip chicken in melted margarine and roll in bread crumbs.
Place in baking dish.
Break up bacon over chicken.
Pour soups over chicken.
Cover and cook in oven on medium heat (350°) for two hours or until tender.
Squeeze a little lemon juice over chicken, if desired.

title: date pudding
directions: Chop dates; pour water over dates.
Cream butter, sugar and egg and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350°.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots for 10 minutes.
Blanch in cold water; cool, then add celery, green pepper and onion.
Mix soup, salad oil, sugar, vinegar, salt, mustard and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and stir.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Fry four slices of bacon until crisp.
Place on a paper towel to drain.
In the bacon fat, brown 1/2 cup chopped green pepper until soft.
Mix together a can of cream-style corn, the bacon (crumbled), green pepper, 3 teaspoons chopped pimentos, a slightly beaten egg and 1/2 can French fried onion rings.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Use remaining onion rings as topping.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in refrigerator.
Eat and enjoy.

title: tangy vegetables
directions: Combine dry salad dressing mix with oil in large casserole dish.
Add vegetables and toss to coat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix ham, pork, milk, egg and oatmeal or bread crumbs and make into balls.
Arrange in baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, vinegar and water and pour over balls.
Bake 1 hour in medium oven at 350°.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix ground chuck, tomato juice and seasoning together.
Add the cheese which has been cubed.
Spread on bread slices and top with strips of cheese.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: burger and beans
directions: Brown the hamburger and 1 onion.
Add chili powder to taste; drain any grease after completely browned.
Add the brown sugar, ketchup and barbecue sauce.
Add some more chili powder, if needed.
Mix and simmer.
Add the pork and beans.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.
Add the last onion; simmer for a couple of minutes.

title: peerless rice-paddy pie(in honor of stallion, "alex miles")
directions: Whip the whipping cream; set aside.
Mix the cream cheese and the sugar until smooth.
Add in the sweetened strawberries and mix by tossing lightly.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first five ingredients.
Put this mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.	Sprinkle with dry cake mix and drizzle with melted margarine.
Top with walnuts.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until knife comes out clean.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: quick layered bean dip
directions: Layer in order given.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed of mixer 5 minutes; gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with finely chopped walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Start at narrow end; roll towel and cake together.
Cool.
Unroll.

title: cereal crunchies
directions: Arrange fruit on top of any ready-to-eat cereal to represent a funny face.
(Use bananas for ears or eyes, apple or pineapple for whole face, strawberry for nose, raisins for eyes or beard, peach slice for mouth.)
Serve with milk.

title: chive-onion-potato bake
directions: Rehydrate potatoes according to package directions.
Drain well.
With a fork or wire whisk, beat eggs, soft cream cheese and milk in a large bowl until blended.
Stir in potatoes, Parmesan and pepper.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish or shallow 10-inch round casserole.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes, until set and lightly browned.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serve as a main dish or cut in small squares for party appetizers.

title: cream cheese pecan pound cake
directions: Reserve 1/3 cup flour to dredge pecans.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat the eggs, then add the sugar.
Then the milk.
Sift together the dry ingredients then mix in along with your choice of vanilla or nutmeg.
Drop the batter from a funnel into 375° deep fat.
Spiral into intricate endless patterns.
Using your finger to stop the flow on the funnel when desired shape is formed. Serve warm with powdered sugar, jelly or cinnamon and sugar.

title: princess loaf
directions: Put in blender sesame seed, milk, onion and parsley.
Blend slightly.
Pour into bowl and mix remaining ingredients well. Place in shallow casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spiced applesauce raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Beat all ingredients, except raisins, in large bowl on medium speed for
1 minute, scraping bowl constantly.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into pan.
Bake
until wooden pick comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove
from
pan; cool before slicing.	Makes one 9-inch loaf.

title: tuna or chicken burgers
directions: Mix filling ingredients.
Fill buttered buns with mixture. Wrap in aluminum foil and refrigerate.
Just before serving, heat at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach manicotti
directions: In large bowl combine Ricotta, spinach, 1 cup Mozzarella, 1/4 cup Parmesan, egg, parsley, onion powder, pepper and garlic powder. Combine spaghetti sauce and water.	Spread 1 cup sauce in an ungreased 9 x 13 baking dish and stuff uncooked manicotti with spinach mixture.
Arrange over sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over manicotti and sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from the refrigerator 30 minutes before baking.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: fig - strawberry preserves
directions: Thoroughly mix figs, Jell-O and sugar in large saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour quickly into jars and seal.

title: mom's butterscotch squares
directions: Can be done on stove top or with microwave.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix with sugar.
Add eggs, vinegar, vanilla and coconut.
Add milk, mixing well.
Stir in meal and mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: sausage crescent rolls
directions: Separate crescent roll dough into triangles.
Place 1 sausage link at wide end of triangle; roll up.
Place on baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 11 to 15 minutes, or until crescent roll is brown.

title: cheese wafers *
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into two long rolls. Refrigerate overnight.
Slice into thin rings and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° until lightly browned (5 to 7 minutes).
Makes about 75 wafers.

title: self filled cupcake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare cake mix according to package directions, adding the instant coffee to the liquid called for on the cake box. Fill paper cupcake cups 2/3 full in muffin tins.

title: mini chips brunch crescents
directions: Unroll crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Sprinkle a heaping tablespoon of mini chips on each triangle and gently press into dough.
Starting at short side of triangle, roll dough to opposite point.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve warm.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to boil the first 4 ingredients.
Boil about 20 minutes or until ball forms in cold water.
Take off stove and add next 3 ingredients.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts (pecans or walnuts) if you like for nutty fudge.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and score with tines of fork.
(Press fork tines into cucumber flesh and peel length of cuke.)
Do not peel.
Slice about 1/8-inch or thickness of your choice.
Slice onions into rings and separate.
Slice or dice green pepper.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Beat yolk and add with milk to pumpkin mixture.
Beat egg white and fold carefully into mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° a few minutes, then bake at 350° until done.

title: peach glaze pie
directions: Mash 1 cup sliced peaches.
Add water and cook 5 minutes.
Mix sugar and cornstarch; add to fruit mixture.
Cook until thick and clear.
Add lemon juice, butter and salt.
Allow mixture to cool completely.
Arrange remaining fruit in cooled pie shell.
Pour cooled glaze over fruit.
Chill thoroughly.
Top with whipped cream.

title: aunt denise's fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit. Slice bananas into large bowl. Add fruit, marshmallows and mayonnaise. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: ham ring
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve in boiling water. Blend in sour cream, salad dressing, vinegar, salt and pepper. Chill until partially set; whip until fluffy.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 5-cup ring mold; chill until firm. Garnish with tomatoes or cheese or pineapple or orange slices. Serves 6.

title: fannie may fudge
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar and stir.
Add milk and heat until fairly warm (not hot).
Add marshmallows.
Bring to a slight boil. Remove from heat and add chocolate and nuts.
Place in buttered jelly roll pan.

title: heavenly hash salad
directions: Mix together and chill for 4 hours.
Drain fruits.
Serves 8.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Heat and serve with nachos.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil for 1 hour.
Let set until room temperature. Add the vanilla and Everclear.
Bottle. Let set 24 hours.

title: split levels
directions: Melt chocolate chips, cream cheese and evaporated milk over low heat or in microwave.
Add walnuts.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Microwave syrup and sugar until it comes to a boil.
Add peanut butter; stir until dissolved.
(I put in microwave for about 1 minute more.)
Pour over Rice Krispies.
Spread evenly into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips for only 2 to 3 minutes in microwave.
Spread over the warm Rice Krispie layer.

title: cheesy tortillas
directions: Spread cream cheese on tortilla.
Top with another tortilla (sandwich).
Cut two tortillas in slices (like a pizza) and place on platter.
Place cup of picante in middle of platter for dipping.
This makes an excellent last minute dish, especially when unexpected company arrives.

title: squash supreme
directions: Saute pepper and onion in oleo.
Drain the squash and while still hot, add ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Drain.
Melt Velveeta cheese in with sausage.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, and enough confectioners sugar to make the dough thick enough to form into balls.
Refrigerate. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Then dip the balls into the chocolate with toothpicks.

title: sicilian spinach pie
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Have a 13 x 9-inch baking dish on hand.
Use 1 tablespoon of olive oil to grease the pan.
In pan, heat the remaining oil and saute onion over medium-low heat for 15 minutes. Add olives and saute an additional 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Cut dough in half and roll out a piece to fit the bottom and sides of the pan.
Press into the pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Place uncooked spinach into Parmesan cheese.
Scatter the onion/olive mixture over the spinach and sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese.
Roll out remaining dough and place on top.
Make 6 to 8 holes in top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until the crust is brown.
Serve at once.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Pare eggplant and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Cook in boiling water with 1/2 teaspoon salt until tender (about 15 minutes). Drain well.
Mash the eggplant into small pieces.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Stir gently.
Add eggs, milk, bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish. Combine margarine and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion in a frying pan.
Add Worcestershire sauce, tomato sauce and barbecue sauce.
Stir well. Sprinkle oregano over mixture.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese over mixture and top with quartered biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until biscuits are brown.

title: caramels
directions: Boil the first five ingredients 5 minutes.
Gradually add milk. Boil and stir continually until firm ball forms in small bowl of water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in food processor or blender.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, cream together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar, beating with electric mixer until smooth, about 2 minutes.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Combine soy sauce, ginger and garlic.
Add beef strips and toss.
