Set aside while preparing vegetables.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Set aside 3/4 cup of crackers. Press remaining crumb mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Set aside. Combine sweetened condensed milk, orange juice concentrate and Mandarin oranges. Mix with mixer. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon mixture over crust and sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture. Cover and freeze until firm.

title: sand pie
directions: Crust:
Melt margarine, mix with flour and add 3/4 cup pecans. Pat out in pie pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Take out of oven. Let cool completely.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Bring to a boil; simmer for 15 minutes.
Can and seal.
Have your jars and lids good and hot.

title: frosted 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add 7-Up.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold in fruit and marshmallows.
Let congeal.

title: low-fat apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix together apple filling, water and granulated sugar in a bowl.
In another mixing bowl, mix together all the dry ingredients.
Fold the two together and spoon into a square baking dish that has been sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Bake about 30 to 40 minutes, until set and golden brown on top.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Mix well all ingredients.

title: crunchy vegetable spread
directions: Place vegetables in a small colander or strainer; drain well. Beat together cream cheese and lemon juice until smooth.
Stir in vegetables and pepper.
Serve on crackers or mini bread sandwiches.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: grandmother's rhubarb custard pie
directions: Let rhubarb stand in water for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Add rhubarb.
Mix and bake in 2 single crusts for 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: fried cabbage
directions: This recipe is great for using up leftover cabbage rolls. Cabbage and meat mixture left over from cabbage rolls.
Cook noodles (1/4 package) drain and add to mixture.
Fry cabbage first and add beef mixture.
Fry on low heat.
You can add hot or sweet peppers.
Add 1/2 jar of chicken gravy to mixture.
Serve and Enjoy!

title: calabaza cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 layers according to package directions.
Simmer raspberries, sugar and water on medium heat until thick and total volume is reduced by half.
Whip cream with vanilla and powdered sugar and add 1/2 coconut.
Layer the cake with raspberry sauce, then 1/4 cup whipped cream mixture.
Place next cake layer on top and repeat process.
"Ice" the cake with the remaining whipped cream and sprinkle the remaining whipped cream on top.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding mix and milk. Add sour cream and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Mix well. Pour mixture over layered bananas and vanilla wafers.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Line with whole graham crackers. Mix pudding and milk.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over crackers.
Alternate, ending with crackers on top. Refrigerate 2 hours before frosting.

title: thanksgiving salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and allow to cool.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Stir into cooled gelatin.
Put in mold and chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; add relish, nuts and celery.
Chill.

title: salmon yule log
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Add cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, liquid smoke and salt; mix well.
Chill 2 or 3 hours or overnight.
Shape into log.
Chill 2 or 3 hours.
Sprinkle pecans on wax paper.
Roll log in pecans.
Chill until ready to serve with crackers.

title: country mashed potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into small portions.
Boil for 30 minutes.
Drain all water and pour into large mixing bowl, then add butter and mix on low until butter has melted.
Slowly add Pet milk and turn up speed to medium.
Add salt and pepper.
Beat until creamy and smooth.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with nonstick spray.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Mash and mix with 1/2 cheese and 1/2 cracker crumbs.
Top with remaining cheese and crackers.
Dot with margarine and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cubed steak in gravy
directions: Salt, pepper and flour steak.
Place in iron skillet frying on medium heat.
Drain well.
After frying all meat, drain off excess grease if any.
Place small onion rings into pan and brown.
Add 1/2 cup plain flour, stirring as you add salt and pepper to taste. Add water or milk to desired consistency of gravy you like.
Place all meat into deep baking dish.
Pour gravy over meat.
Cover and place in oven for 1 hour on 200° to 250°.
Serve over rice.
Steak will be tender and tasty.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix and store in covered jar.
Put 3 teaspoonfuls per cup. Fill with boiling water.

title: delicious orange jello mold
directions: Pour boiling water into Jell-O.
Add frozen orange juice. Add crushed pineapple with juice.
Let stand in fridge until it starts to jell or coats a spoon.
Mash bananas; mix in Jell-O and fold in Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Pour into oiled mold or a 9 x 13 pan or pour into nice glass bowl.
Chill firm.
Best if made day before.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large skillet, cook sausage over moderate heat until it is broken into small pieces and is no longer pink.
Drain and mix with parsley and 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese, scallions and lightly beaten eggs.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a large skillet and saute mushroom caps briefly, rolling them around in the pan.
Cool.
Divide mixture among mushroom caps, mounding it slightly.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a large lightly buttered pan at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Melt butter, stir in flour.
Gradually add half-and-half, stir until thickened.
Add Parmesan; cook and stir until smooth.
Fold in crabmeat, heat 3 minutes, stir occasionally.
Toss fettucini with sauce, sprinkle with parsley.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: refreshing cucumber dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except cucumbers, mixing until well blended.
Stir in cucumbers.
Chill several hours or overnight. Serve with chips or vegetable dippers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion, then drain.
Add salt, pepper, egg, chicken soup and dressing mix.
Then mix all ingredients and add cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Add orange juice, then add all the other ingredients.
Refrigerate for a few hours before serving.

title: chocolate chip pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, combine the flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda. In another bowl, beat the eggs, sugar, pumpkin and oil. Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. Fold in chocolate chips. Pour into 2 greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks. Yield: 2 loaves.

title: chicken broccoli fettuccine
directions: In skillet in hot margarine, cook garlic for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in soup, milk and cheese.
Heat to boiling.
Add chicken.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Toss with fettuccine.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes and fresh parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: angel's biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients, then cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk. Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to mixture.
Knead lightly. Roll out; cut with biscuit cutter and bake on greased cookie sheet at 450° about 10 to 12 minutes.
Dough may be stored in refrigerator, pinching off as much as is needed each time or may be cut, then frozen.
Yields 5 dozen biscuits.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time beating well after each one.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk to the chocolate mixture.
Beat well each time.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 3 deep 8 or 9-inch cake pans, lined on bottom with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost tops only.

title: nacho dip
directions: Melt cheese
with
milk.
Add taco sauce.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add ground beef to cheese mixture.
Keep warm and serve with nacho chips.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Melt butter in iron skillet. (Be sure to use iron skillet.)
Add sugar mixture to melted butter.
Beat egg yolks. Add milk and beat together.
Add this, a little at a time, to sugar mixture in skillet, stirring constantly.
Cook slowly. When thick enough, add vanilla.
Place in baked deep dish pie shell. Top with meringue.
Place in slow oven at 325° until meringue is brown.

title: baked vegetable medley
directions: Separate cauliflower and broccoli into florets.
Cut carrots into 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Into a casserole dish, that has been sprayed with vegetable oil, place vegetables evenly.
Slice butter into several "pats" and place on top of mixture.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until tender.

title: ham loaf with pineapple
directions: Mix thoroughly the ham, pork, pepper, cracker crumbs, eggs, pineapple juice and onion.
Arrange 2 slices of pineapple along each side of a greased Pyrex loaf pan.
Put ham mixture into loaf pan, pressing against the pineapple slices to hold them in place. Cut remaining pineapple slices into fifths and place on top of ham loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken and vegetable salad
directions: Chop chicken up in bite size and fry until done after seasoning and flouring.
Remove all grease from skillet.
Open frozen vegetables and pour into bowl.
Mix chicken and dressing and vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight for best results.

title: monster chocolate chip cookies
directions: In mixing bowl (using a wooden spoon) or in the large bowl of an electric mixer, cream the butter and shortening together until well-blended and soft.
Then beat in sugars in turn, beating well after each until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time, then beat in vanilla.

title: idaho potato cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, beating well. Blend in potatoes and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Add alternately with milk, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix just to blend.
Turn onto lightly floured surface; knead gently for 20 turns.
Roll or pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with 3-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet and bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 100 biscuits.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef. Add celery. Cook 10 minutes. Stir often. Add remaining ingredients, except green peppers and cheeses. Simmer, covered, 20 minutes. Add green pepper; cover and cook 10 minutes. When serving, add both cheeses on top of soup in bowl.

title: jello salad
directions: Make jello and cool.
Drain pineapple, mix with cottage cheese and nuts.
Add to cooled jello then stir in the whipped topping and refrigerate.

title: roast opossum supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients and stuff opossum with it.
Sew up opening with large needle and coarse thread.
Roast in oven roaster on wire rack at 350° until tender and richly brown.

title: green fried tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in 1/2-inch thick slices.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip tomatoes in mixture, covering both sides.
Fry slowly in small amount of hot fat until browned; turn and brown other side.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Beat sour cream into cream cheese.
Beat lemon juice and Italian seasoning into mixture.

title: meat loaf diabetic
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: festive cranberry salad
directions: In bowl, combine milk and lemon juice. Mix well. Stir in the pineapple, cranberry sauce, marshmallows, pecans
and food coloring, if desired. Fold in the whipped topping. Spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight. Cut into squares. Yield: 12-16 servings.

title: cracklin' corn bread
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add egg and buttermilk, stirring mixture just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in cracklings.
Place in a well-greased 10-inch cast-iron skillet in a 450° oven for 4 minutes, or until hot. Remove from oven.
Pour batter into skillet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix sugar and Jell-O in hot water.
Add cold water, lemonade and pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: christmas candies
directions: Butter sides of a heavy 2 quart saucepan.
In it combine sugar and milk.
Heat and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to a boil.
Then cook to soft-ball stage (234 degrees).
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients and stir until blended.
Pour into buttered 9x9x2-inch pan.
Score in squares when warm, cut when firm.

title: porky pine meatballs
directions: 1st Layer: 2 cans (drained and blended) Trappy's jalapeno pinto beans.

title: cajun delight
directions: In a large pan, combine all ingredients.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove lid and simmer an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: lobster dip
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter or margarine.
Then add remaining ingredients.

title: pineapple cheese dish
directions: Stir together pineapple and grated cheese.
Mix sugar and flour; sprinkle over pineapple and cheese.
Sprinkle margarine and crushed Ritz crackers over pineapple dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Follow instructions on jello box, then fold in whipped cream. Stir in remainder of ingredients; place in fridge for 2 1/2 hours. Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: hilda's boiled custard peach ice cream
directions: Beat all ingredients, except peaches.
Cook on low heat until it's showing thickness, stirring all the time.
When custard is done, add peaches.
Put into ice cream freezer and freeze or you can put in the freezer.

title: wild rice and duck
directions: Boil chunks of duck breasts until tender; discard water. Cook rice as directed on package. Brown sausage and onion. Mix all ingredients; pour in greased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole(microwave)
directions: Cut up 1 chicken into small pieces and salt and pepper it. Place rice in bottom of Dutch oven.
Add 1 can of mushroom soup, 1 can of water and stir.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice and soup.
Cook on High for 15 minutes.
Then cook on Medium-Low setting for 25 minutes.
Let stand for 15 to 20 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: garden club chicken
directions: Combine chicken and all ingredients. Mix gently. Place in casserole dish.

title: almost snickers
directions: Mix. Shape into bar. Wrap in foil. Freeze until firm.
Makes 1 serving. Exchanges: 1 milk, 1 fruit, 1 bread, 1 protein and 1 fat.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Put sugar, syrup and water on stove to boil.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Let syrup cook until it forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Pour slowly into egg whites, beating constantly with mixer.
Add vanilla and beat as long as possible. Drop by spoon on wax paper.
Set bowl in hot water if candy begins to harden.
(May add nuts.)

title: zucchini saute
directions: Combine zucchini and salt; let stand 15 minutes.
Rinse in cold water and drain well.
Saute onion in butter until tender. Add zucchini.
Cook, stirring constantly until all liquid is absorbed.
Stir in sour cream and pepper.

title: mae's sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg, beat until fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Add dry ingredients into creamed mixture and blend well.
Divide dough in half.
Chill 1 hour.
On floured surface, roll out dough 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in shapes.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool and decorate. Yields 2 dozen.

title: play dough
directions: Stir together and cook over heat until mixture starts to come away from sides, approximately 2 minutes.
Knead.
Add coloring before cooking.
Store in covered container.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cook squash and onion in slight amount of water until tender. Mash.
Add other ingredients; sprinkle with crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first 8 ingredients.
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Spoon into a well-greased cake pan or a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until cake tests done.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: orange shortcake
directions: Section oranges, removing seeds. Save extra juice and make up to 1 cup with concentrated orange juice. Mix flour and sugar; add 1 cup orange juice and cook until boils. Let boil a few minutes and add butter and stir in. Cool to room temperature. Stack rounds with sections, between and over top with sweetened cream. Serve at room temperature.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Place pineapple and juice in pan.
Bring to a boil; add lime Jell-O and dissolve.
Fold in cheese.
Cool slightly; fold in whipping cream.
Chill and cut in squares.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in a 2-quart boiler.
Stir in milk and butter.
Cook until mixture comes to a rolling boil; stir well. Continue to cook on high for 1 minute.
Remove mixture and stir in vanilla.
Add oats; mix thoroughly.
Add coconut and nuts (optional).
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator to set.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown
chicken	that
has
been
sprinkled
with Tony's seasoning.	The more you use, the spicier the chicken.
Remove chicken
from skillet.
Saute chopped onion and bell pepper in chicken
grease
(2 tablespoons).
Place chicken back in skillet. Pour
tomatoes
over
chicken.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally to avoid sticking.
Serve over hot yellow rice.

title: sultana cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs and lemon extract.
Mix. Add flour and baking powder.
Mix together.
Add nuts and raisins last; mix well.
Put in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: orange glaze
directions: Combine brown sugar, orange juice and mustard.
Mix well. Spoon over ham, shoulder roast, (pork) etc.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine sour cream and margarine.
Fold in flour.
Fill greased muffin tins three-fourths full.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 18 biscuits.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, salt and 1/2 cup boiling water in saucepan; simmer, covered, for 15 minutes or until tender.
Pour off all but 1/4 cup stock; dot with butter.
Combine orange juice, corn syrup and brown sugar.
Blend well.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Simmer, basting frequently for 15 minutes.

title: delicious pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and butter in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly until butter is melted. Remove from heat and add hot syrup to beaten eggs, stirring constantly. Add pecans and vanilla extract to mixture. Pour filling into pie shell. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In a separate bowl, put flour, baking powder, baking soda and sugar. Cut in shortening; add yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Knead slightly.
Roll out to 1/2-inch; cut 15 biscuits.
Place into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan and brush with butter.
Let rise 30 minutes or in refrigerator overnight.
Bake until golden brown.

title: t's dole golden layer cake
directions: Combine undrained pineapple, whipped topping and pudding mix. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Cut cake lengthwise into 3rds.
Spread 1/3 pudding mixture over each layer of cake, ending with pudding on top.
Chill 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds.
Serves 12.

title: souperburgers
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain excess fat.
Add soup and seasonings, simmer about 5 to 10 minutes to blend flavors, stirring occasionally.
Serve on buns.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Drain pimentos and chop parsley.
Combine with dressing in a large Ziploc bag; add mushrooms and toss to coat.
Chill.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into greased casserole.
Top with 1/2 cup of grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. May serve with crackers.

title: aunt louise's banana salad
directions: Mix sugar, salt, milk and egg together.
Cook until thick. Let cool.
Add vinegar and peanut butter.
Cut up bananas and pour dressing over them.
Sprinkle with peanuts.

title: refrigerator crock salad
directions: Mix well and pour over all ingredients.
Put in a crock or covered dish.
Let stand in the refrigerator.
"The longer it stands, the better it is."

title: cabbage soup
directions: Put the bacon pieces in pan and fry until almost done.
Then add all other ingredients, except hamburger meat.
I add that about 30 minutes before soup is done.
You may also add carrots, English peas, corn or any other vegetable you would like, but if you add extra vegetables, you will also need to add extra liquid. Cook about 1 1/2 hours.

title: as good as fudge(diabetic)
directions: In small pan over low heat stir together honey and peanut butter until smooth.
Remove from heat; add cocoa powder and blend well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Press into greased 9 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 36 squares.

title: marjorie boyd's pea salad
directions: Cook peas; drain.
Mix ingredients and chill.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken, debone and retain broth (1 1/2 to 2 cups). Prepare rice with equal parts water in 2 to 3-quart pan.
Melt margarine and mix in flour.
Add broth slowly, stirring constantly, then melt cheese in the sauce.
Defrost broccoli and cut into small pieces.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil; add rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet; saute onion and celery until tender.
In a large mixing bowl, combine rice, celery and onion with remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gingerbread people
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar and butter.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Roll dough on well-floured board.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Decorate as desired.
Makes about 15 (6-inch) cookies.

title: homemade syrup
directions: Mix in pan; turn to boil. Boil 1 minutes; turn off. Add Maple and vanilla.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly butter, shortening, confectioners sugar, egg and flavorings.
Blend in flour and salt. Divide dough in half; blend food coloring into one half.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Pick over and wash cranberries.
Put through food chopper using fine blade; mix in half as much mashed ripe banana.
Sweeten with honey and beat well.
Let stand for an hour or so before serving.

title: pretzels
directions: Mix yeast, warm water and sugar until dissolved.
Stir in salt and flour gradually.
Dump dough onto breadboard and knead until smooth.
Shape into pretzels by rolling pieces of dough into long ropes and twist into pretzel shape.
Place on oiled cookie sheets. Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with kosher salt.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: no peel chicken
directions: Stir rice and soups together in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Lay chicken pieces on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and poultry seasoning or paprika.
(Sesame seed may also be sprinkled on top.)
Cover with foil and place in oven at 350° for 1 hour. Don't peek!

title: good cherry salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice and pudding mix in bowl; mix well.
Add banana, pie filling and undrained pineapple; toss to mix.
Pour into serving bowl.
Chill until set.
May substitute any fruit juice for pineapple juice.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: pecan slices
directions: Mix these ingredients; spread about 1/8-inch thick on the 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Melt chocolate morsels over hot water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and syrup.
Blend in bourbon.
Combine nuts and wafers. Add to chocolate mix.
Shape into balls.
Roll in powdered or granulated sugar.
Store in container several days to ripen.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar, Karo and cornstarch together.
Cook until thickened.
Add Jell-O and mix well.
Cool and pour part in bottom of baked pie shell.
Leave strawberries whole and pour remainder of mixture over strawberries.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside. Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Add half the flour mixture and half the milk. Mix well.

Mix in rest of flour mixture and milk until smooth. Fill a greased and floured baking pan or 2 layer pans no more than half full. Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes until cake springs up when lightly touched in center.

title: hawaiian bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Serve with Hawaiian bread.

title: apricot bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9-inch square pan.
In medium bowl, beat butter until creamy.
Stir in sugar and brown sugar. Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Stir until mixture is crumbly. Set aside 1 cup of crumb mixture for top.
Press remaining mixture into pan.
Stir lemon juice into apricot preserves.
Spread into pan, leaving a 4-inch border around all edges.
Sprinkle preserves with remaining 1 cup crumb mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until browned.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Bake cake mix in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chocolate boil cookies
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients about 3 to 4 minutes. Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: applesauce raisin bread
directions: Combine applesauce and soda in a small bowl. Cream butter with sugar in large bowl. Stir in egg, cinnamon, salt, allspice and cloves. Blend in applesauce mixture. Mix in flour and raisins. Pour into greased 5 x 9 loaf pan or use smaller pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool 10 minutes in pan on rack.
Take out of pan and cool on rack completely.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat.
Add flour.
Slowly stir in 2 cups of milk.
When slightly thickened, slowly add rest of milk, chicken granules, broccoli and cheese.
Stir until smooth and thick.
Enjoy!

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit cocktail, juice and all, with pudding until pudding is thick.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Add well drained pineapple and marshmallows.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: pecan roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in wax paper and refrigerate.
Cool and slice.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
In a medium saucepan, simmer 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serves 5.

title: grilled pico burgers
directions: In bowl combine all ingredients.
Divide meat mixture into 4 hamburger patties.
Sear 5 inches from hot coals for 2 minutes. Turn and cook for 6 minutes for medium done.
Serve hot, topped with avocado, onion, lettuce and tomato.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Top with cheese cracker crumbs rolled in 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in airtight jar.
Place 2 to 3 teaspoons of tea mixture in 3/4 cup boiling water.
May be made in larger quantities, adding 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Cut boneless venison into thin, small steaks.
Sprinkle with garlic and onion salt; pound well.
Roll in flour and brown meat in skillet.
Alternate layers of meat, cream of mushroom soup and sliced onion in a casserole.
Add 1 soup can of water over all. Cover and bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix rice and soup together in a 2-quart baking dish.
Add drained mushrooms; top with sliced margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ziti with broccoli
directions: Boil broccoli 10 minutes until tender.
Drain.
Cook ziti 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Saute garlic in olive oil in large skillet until lightly browned.
Add broccoli; cook 1 minute.
Add ziti, cream and Parmesan and cook 2 minutes, tossing well.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan and top with Mozzarella.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: texas brisket of beef
directions: Spread the brisket generously with the Adolph's meat tenderizer; pierce with a fork.
Place in a large rectangular Pyrex dish.

title: lorna doone dessert
directions: Mix crushed Lorna Doones and melted margarine.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh peach or apple crisp
directions: Peel 5 to 6 peaches or apple slices into small slices and place in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Melt margarine; add sugar and flour.
(This will be dry and crumbly.)
Sprinkle over fruit and pat down.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Crumble 1 1/2 slices of toasted bread into crab meat and combine ingredients with milk blended with mayonnaise.
With other 1 1/2 slices of toasted bread, grate and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Dot butter on top. Put in stove and cook until warm through.
Serve.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Heat slowly in double boiler.
Dip balls in this mixture.

title: lucky lemon ice cream(makes 1 gallon.)
directions: Combine the sugar, milk, half and half, whipping cream and lemon rind.
Add lemon juice and beat well.
Fold in egg whites. Add food coloring, if desired.
Pour into freezer can of 1 gallon hand or electric freezer.
Let ripen at least 2 hours.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add rest of ingredients; simmer 1 hour.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Combine all ingredients (place sugar in mixture first, then melted butter).
Place mixture in greased baking dish.
Place in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp, chicken and vegetable fettuccine
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions until al dente; drain and toss lightly with 1 tablespoon olive oil and keep warm. Cut zucchini, bell pepper, carrots and green onions into julienne strips.
Heat remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil in large skillet. Saute garlic lightly; add zucchini, bell pepper, carrots and green onions.
Cook, tossing, until crisp-tender.
Add chicken strips; cook, stirring, until opaque (about 3 minutes).
Add shrimp; cook, tossing, until opaque (about 1 to 2 minutes).
Stir in wine, hot pepper flakes, lime zest and cilantro.
Bring to boil quickly; pour over cooked pasta in serving bowl.
Toss to combine.
Garnish with minced fresh parsley.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.
Also may be served over rice.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Beat well and add flour.
Let rise to almost double in bulk.
Punch down and roll out on lightly floured board to 1/4 inch in thickness.
Cut in about 2-inch pieces.
Dip each piece in melted butter.

title: ruth's chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add one egg at a time.
Add milk, corn meal, vinegar, lemon juice and salt.
Pour into crust.
Cook 10 minutes at 375°, then reduce heat to 325° and cook 40 minutes more.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Pour mixed ingredients over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
(Turn or shake chicken to make sure all chicken pieces are coated.)
Place chicken in baking dish and bake at 300° about an hour or can be grilled.
(Discard marinade, do not cook chicken in the mixture.)

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add dry mixture in small amounts to egg mixture until all ingredients are well blended. Add vanilla.
Blend in carrots, pineapple and pecans. Bake in 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Check at 25 minutes.
Ice with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: so refreshing punch
directions: Mix all juices as directed on package. Next, mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate until ready to use. Add 1 quart of ginger ale. Yields 2 gallons.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix juice and milk together.
Add other ingredients.
Put in a pie shell and chill.
Makes 2 or 3 pies.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together butter and shortening.
Beat in 1 1/2 cups sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Shape rounded teaspoons of dough into small balls.
Combine 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; roll balls in sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
(Be careful, they burn easily!!) Remove from baking sheet; cool on racks.
Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: ranch style pasta
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Put in saucepan.
Stir in olive oil on low-medium heat.
Add package dressing.
Stir in veggies.
Heat until veggies are tender.
Serve.

title: vegetable frittata
directions: Thinly slice the onion and mince the garlic.
Cut the squash and zucchini into 1/4-inch slices.
Seed the bell peppers and cut into 1/4-inch strips.
Slice the mushrooms.
Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add the vegetables.
Saut the vegetables for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Whisk the eggs and cream in a large bowl.
Add the salt and pepper.
Add the bread cubes, cream cheese and Swiss cheese and mix well.
Add the sauted vegetables and mix well.
Pour into a greased 10-inch spring-form pan or a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, packing the mixture firmly.
Place the pan on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until firm to the touch, puffed and golden brown.
Cover the top with foil to prevent overbrowning if necessary.
Place the spring-form pan on a serving plate.
Loosen the frittata from the side and remove the side of the pan.
Cut into small squares. Serve the frittata hot, at room temperature or cold.
May reheat cooked frittata at 350° for 15 minutes or until warmed through, if desired.
Yield:
48 small appetizers.

title: orange-ginger pork roast
directions: * Will leave some leftovers for sandwiches.
